title: carrot cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 325° in a greased tube pan for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions on package.
Add sugar and stir with Jell-O to dissolve.
Use pineapple juice as part of cold liquid.
Using food processor or grinder, chop cranberries, whole orange with peeling (remove seeds) and English walnuts.
Add to Jell-O mixture and place in refrigerator to set for at least four hours or overnight.
This will keep well for several days.

title: cheesy chili rice(prep:  10 minutes; cook:  55 minutes; serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice according to package directions. In a small bowl mix sour cream and chilies.
In a buttered 1 1/2-quart to 2-quart baking dish alternate layers of cooked rice, Jack cheese and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese evenly over top.
Bake, uncovered, until mixture is bubbly and cheese on top begins to brown, about 35 minutes.

title: meat and potatoes
directions: Fry diced potatoes, then fry hamburger meat.
Combine the two and serve.

title: rigatoni with sausage
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; saute sausage, onion and garlic until meat is browned.
Add mushrooms, bay leaf, salt, pepper, tomato paste, water, oregano and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in salted water until tender.
Drain, but not too dry; leave a little to make vegetables juicy.

title: chili
directions: Cut up the tomatoes.
Fry sausage, hamburger, onions and green pepper together.
Combine all ingredients and cook for 2 hours or all day in crock-pot.

title: never-fail pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Sift the flour and salt together.
Add 3 eggs and half of the dry ingredients to butter and sugar.
Add 3 more eggs and remainder of dry ingredients.
Add 2 more eggs and beat until all are well blended.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/4 hours, until firm.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and sour cream.
(Make sure butter is soft before mixing ingredients together.)
Then combine all dry ingredients (baking powder, baking soda, flour and salt).
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Mix all together.
In separate bowl mix chopped nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Using tube pan sprinkle some nut mixture on bottom and then add half cake batter, then some more nut mixture, then rest of cake batter, then rest of nut mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Beat peanut butter and oleo.
Add sugar and roll into balls and refrigerate.
Microwave chocolate chips and shaved wax.
Using toothpicks, dip chilled peanut butter balls into somewhat cooled chocolate.
Close over toothpick holes.

title: jayne's submix
directions: Chop the meat and cheeses and add 1 jar sweet cherry peppers. Mix with tomatoes, onions and shredded lettuce.
(Use as many tomatoes, onion and shredded lettuce as you want.)
Mix olive oil, and pepper juice and then pour over all ingredients (use your judgment on amount of liquid).
Sprinkle with oregano.
Serve with fresh rolls.

title: secret recipe salad dressing
directions: Mix soup and ketchup; add vinegar and sugar alternately.
Stir in all the rest except oil.
Add it last and mix well.
It may be quite thick.
Can add 2 cups water or thin as needed.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Leaving skins on, slice baked potatoes in half and arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of potatoes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy no bake cheesecake
directions: Cream the butter until smooth.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Whip 2 egg whites with salt until stiff peaks are formed.
Add vanilla.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Turn into two 8-inch pie shells.
Bake in a moderately hot 425° oven about 12 minutes.
Now decrease heat to 300° and bake about 20 minutes longer or until a silver knife blade inserted into center comes out clean.
Beat the remaining 6 egg whites with a dash of salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Add the 12 tablespoons of sugar, two at a time, while continuing to beat until stiff peaks form.
Beat in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on the pies and return to 300° oven for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Very rich.

title: lavender lemonade
directions: Stir together water, lemon juice, sugar and grape juice until sugar is dissolved.
Chill several hours.
In container of blender, process lemon mixture and egg white 2 to 3 minutes until frothy.
Serve over crushed ice.
Makes 4 cups.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard and salt in gallon jar.
Place cucumbers in jars.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and seal.
Let stand 3 weeks before eating.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together 1/4 cup sugar, pretzels (crushed) and margarine; place in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Let crust cool.
Next layer:
cream cheese (softened), 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip; mix together and pour over crust.

title: rich's lace cookies
directions: Blend flour and nuts.
In saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and butter.
Bring to a boil, over moderate heat, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add flour; mix gradually.
Cool slightly.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix cream of chicken, sour cream and poppy seed together and spread on top of chicken.
Crush 24 Ritz crackers and put over mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed over top.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Combine rice, salt and pepper in greased 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with onion powder.
Add mushrooms and juice.
Arrange chicken on top.
Add bouillon and water.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab ball
directions: Thaw the frozen crab and drain.
Blend all the ingredients together except the nuts.
Shape into a log or ball.
Roll log or ball in the chopped pecans; refrigerate.
Serve with crackers. This is a favorite of ours.

title: dove casserole
directions: Place whole doves in broth and simmer, covered, until tender. Remove breasts and dice meat; return to broth.
Blend 3 tablespoons butter with flour and sour cream.
Saute breadcrumbs, vegetables, parsley and sage in 3 tablespoons butter.
Combine breadcrumb mixture and thickened cream with dove meat in skillet. Season with salt and pepper.
Add sherry and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Transfer to casserole and broil for a few minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over hash brown squares.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°; covered first 1/2 hour and uncovered last 1/2 hour.

title: trader's punch
directions: Combine orange juice, lemon juice and grenadine syrup.
Pour over ice into punch bowl.
Just before serving, pour ginger ale down side of bowl.
Add orange (or lemon) slices and berries. Serve.

title: stewed catfish
directions: Clean catfish very well.
Take slime off by rubbing salt onto fish; rinse well.
Cut into serving pieces.
Simmer tomatoes, onion, vinegar, water, salt and pepper until saucy consistency. Add catfish and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, salt, pepper and melted butter; mix well.
Layer about 1/3 of the crumbs in a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover with half the oysters and oyster liquor.
Add half the cream.
Add another third of crumbs and follow with a layer of remaining oysters, liquid and cream. Top with remaining crumbs and sprinkle with mace.
Dot generously with Roquefort cheese.
Bake in hot oven until oysters are cooked and top is crisp and browned, about 30 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash, then simmer lentils.
Along with the lentils, simmer vegetables and meat for about a half hour.
(This is an old Pennsylvania Dutch recipe.)

title: aunt sally's cocoa drops
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost when cooled.

title: canned green beans
directions: Mix water, vinegar and salt in large kettle.
Bring to a boil. Add beans.
Bring to a boil and boil for 25 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Cover with vinegar water and seal.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese with dry Ranch dressing mix.
Form into a ball, sprinkle with black pepper.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Mix bananas (sliced) and pineapple.
Slice large apple into chunks.
Drain fruit cocktail; may add nuts, marshmallows or coconut.
Combine with fresh strawberries or 2 packages frozen.

title: fancy rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a covered casserole dish at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cold cherry soup
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice to make liquid.
Place liquid in saucepan and add cherries, cinnamon and sugar and simmer gently for 7 minutes.
Blend flour with 3 tablespoons water until smooth; add 3 tablespoons more water to thin and stir into soup.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Chill.
Stir in cream and wine when cool.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Make cake as directions on box.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. While cake is still hot pour over pineapple with juice over cake. Refrigerate until quite cold.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients, except boiling water and soda, together all at once.
Add the boiling water and soda; blend well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix everything together and bake in a well-greased and floured pan, lined with heavy paper.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Do not drain vegetables.
Heat all in crock-pot or on top of stove in pot.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.
Delicious.

title: danish cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in 1 egg at a time. Sift flour with soda and salt. Add alternately with milk and orange juice. Add orange rind, vanilla, dates and nuts. Bake at 325° in tube pan 1 hour or until done. Put topping on cake slowly while hot.

title: chellie's pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake in 325° oven 45 minutes until center is firm.

title: do ahead hamburgers
directions: Add water to onion soup mix.
Mix with ground chuck.
Shape into 12 patties; wrap separately and freeze.
Thaw when ready to use.

title: super homemade popcorn crunch
directions: Coat one cob of popcorn with butter until all cracks are filled between kernels.
Place cob upright on ends inside a brown bag.
Fold top over one time only, causing cob to stand upright inside the bag.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in bowl.
Heat margarine, cocoa and Coke to boiling.
Pour over flour; add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Beat until smooth.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheesy breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease or spray a 9 x 13 pan.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Empty cake mix into bowl with flour.
Mix eggs, oil and water together.
Add to cake mix.
Mix until well blended.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased baking sheets. Flatten slightly with fingers.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
This recipe can also make drop cookie.
Add anything such as chips, nuts, raisins, coconut, etc.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating after each one.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Bake 80
minutes in a 325° oven.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add juice/water mixture.
Set aside 2 cups of jello mixture.
Chill until firm.
Add Cool Whip with reserved mixture when it reaches egg white consistency.
Add chopped nuts.
Spread over firm jello layer.
Chill until firm. Wait until biggest mixture is set then pour 2 cups mixture over and refrigerate.
Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken stew
directions: Stew meat until tender.
Remove bones.
Add vegetables to meat; add seasonings.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add butter and bread crumbs to thicken.
Serve hot.
Add water as necessary.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage,	onion
and
green pepper.
Mix with 3/4 cup sugar.
Let
this mixture stand until you mix and bring to a boil the
other	ingredients.
Pour
this
over the shredded mixture and mix well.
Let stand and chill in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours,
before serving.
Keep refrigerated.
This will keep about 2 weeks.

title: malt shop pie
directions: Save a little Cool Whip for topping if desired.
Save a little crushed Whopper candy for garnish.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and cull cranberries.
Run through grinder on medium blade.
Run orange through, peeling and all (remove pulp).

title: creme de menthe dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows in double boiler with milk.
Cool.
Whip the cream and add to cooled marshmallows.
Fold in creme de menthe. Place half of the crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mixture.
Add remaining crumbs to top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crab soup
directions: Add all ingredients to large pot, except crabmeat.
Simmer for one hour.
Add crabmeat.
Simmer 10 more minutes.
Serve.

title: orange squares
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted margarine and pat in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
This takes about 2 months.
Add gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 405°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, add 2 rabbits, but do this only if necessary because most people don't like to find hair in their stew.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Mix hamburger with cheese and Ro-Tel.
Crush Doritos and mix with lettuce and tomato salad. Pour Ro-Tel dip over lettuce and tomato salad just before you eat.

title: betty's bread
directions: Measure water into a large bowl.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and turn out on floured surface to knead.
When smooth and elastic, place dough back in greased bowl.
Turn dough so greased side is on top.
Cover with cloth and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down and let rise again for 1/2 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put liquid ingredients together in crock-pot.
Brown ground beef; drain well.
Saute pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter. Add to ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low overnight or on medium for 4 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add both kinds of corn and bread mix.
Gently mix with fork.
Stir in eggs. Drop sour cream by tablespoons in different places over corn mixture and gently fold in. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until mixture is firm.
Let cool slightly.
Cut into squares or spoon out.

title: heavenly onions(if you like french onion soup, you will love this recipe.)
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Spread grated cheese over onions.
Mix soup, milk, pepper and soy sauce.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Using the tip of a knife, gently jiggle in several spots to let some of the mixture go down into the onions.
Overlap bread slices on top in a ring, buttered side up.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Push bread slices down slightly into sauce.

title: easy hamburger stew
directions: Add other vegetables like zucchini slices if desired.

title: marinated chicken kabobs
directions: Stir dressing, orange juice and oil in a large bowl.
Add chicken and vegetables; toss to coat.
Cover; refrigerate 3 hours. Heat broiler or grill.
Arrange chicken and vegetables on skewer. Broil 3 inches from heat about 15 minutes or until cooked through, turning frequently and basting with remaining mix.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sharp cheese, mixing well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts or shredded dried beef.

title: polynesian chicken(servings:  12)
directions: In large, shallow roasting pan, put chicken, skin side up. Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Pour syrup and soy sauce over chicken.
Add garlic.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste and turn often.
Pour liquid from chicken into saucepan and add sweet and sour sauce to this.
Boil until sauce thickens and is reduced to about 3 1/2 cups (about 30 minutes).
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Next day, in 350° oven, bake chicken, uncovered, basting often, for 30 minutes. Then add fruit and bake and baste 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
Can add toasted almonds to cooked rice.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together all, except ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale.

title: chinese hamburg
directions: Cook hamburg and onions partially; add celery and cook partially.
Add water, bean sprouts, soy sauce and heat through. Add soups and heat.
Add rice and cook uncovered 10 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: summer spaghetti
directions: Place all the ingredients (except the spaghetti) in a bowl and mix.
Cook spaghetti in rapidly boiling water, not until it's mush but when it's ever so slightly hard.
Drain.
In a large bowl mix the sauce and spaghetti (steaming hot) well.
Put it on the table, pour a glass of wine and enjoy!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Place in bowl.
Combine sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool slightly. Pour over all other ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mona newbern's potatoes and onions
directions: Peel 1 pound of potatoes and cut in thick slices.
Fry over medium heat until done (does not have to be brown).
Drain potatoes and pour off all oil except enough for gravy (about 1/4 cup).
Brown 1 teaspoon of flour in remaining oil.
Return potatoes and 1 chopped onion.
Add water (about 1/2 cup) and simmer slowly for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together 2 eggs, 2 cups powdered sugar and 2 sticks melted margarine for 15 minutes and spread over graham cracker crust. Slice bananas and place over mixture.
Spread drained crushed pineapple next and then the Cool Whip over all. Dribble chocolate syrup and sprinkle chopped nuts across. Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate to set.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bread chicken breasts with bread crumbs.
Fry them in a skillet with peanut oil until they are brown on both sides.
In a baking pan, lay them in spaghetti sauce and cover with cheese. Bake at 350° to 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
The chicken should have almost fully cooked when it was fried.

title: time saver dinner
directions: Prepare dinner according to directions on package.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, onion, pepper and garlic.
Sprinkle about 4 tablespoons chili pepper on top.
Add tomatoes.
Add 1 tomato can full of water. Simmer 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add beans, juice and all.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: cool cookies
directions: Add sprinkles, M&M's and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Add cream cheese, powdered sugar and melted margarine.

title: nanny's roast
directions: Wash roast; cover with onion salt.
Place in pan.
Add Lipton onion mix over roast and 2 cups of water.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery, sliced each one, around the roast.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Cook 1 hour at 400°.
After cooking, use the remaining juice and add it to 2 packages of gravy mix.

title: brunswick stew for the '50's graduates
directions: In Dutch oven, mix pork and beef barbecue, corn and tomatoes. Shred chicken with fingers and stir into mix. Turn on medium. Saute onion in butter and add to mixture. Add pepper and hot sauce. Reduce heat to low, stirring occasionally. Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: fresh orange salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, JELLO, Manadarin oranges and pineapple. Fold in whipped topping.
Chill.
Can be served on lettuce leaves with Ritz or saltine crackers with green cherry on top.
(Serves 8.)

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients together 1 or 2 days before planning to serve. Store in refrigerator.
On morning of serving, stir in large carton of Cool Whip.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown and drain fat.
Add onion, lightly brown.
Add tomatoes, breaking up, and chili, corn and potatoes.
Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Easily doubled.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add egg and mix well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Pour into Pam-sprayed 11 X 7 inch pan. Top with blueberries (or frozen huckleberries) sprinkle cinnamon crumbs over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serve warm.
8 to 10 servings.

title: louise's clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan.
Thin with additional clam juice if necessary for good spreading consistency. Pour into a chafing dish, keeping warm to serve with crackers or toasted bread rounds.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread 2 tablespoons of soup mixture on flour tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese and onion; add a spoonful of hamburger.
Roll; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After all tortillas are filled, pour the remainder of soup mixture, onions and cheese over the top.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water in blender.
Over low heat, melt marshmallows; cool.
Add pineapple, mayonnaise and milk.
Pour into mold and let set.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in butter or margarine, then in mixture of cracker crumbs, sesame seed, salt and pepper.
Place on foil-lined pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until well blended.
Add milk, pineapple and bread.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle slivered almonds and paprika on top. Heat 15 minutes at 325°.

title: yarbi's poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until turns white.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Steam broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together, except crackers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble crackers on top and drizzle with butter.
Bake in a casserole dish at 375° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Can be served over white or yellow rice.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add pecans; mix well.
Spoon into tart shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: steak new orleans
directions: Mix all ingredients (except steak, salt and pepper).
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Brush meat with hot sauce and grill over medium hot coals for 15 minutes on each side.
Baste frequently with sauce.
Season with salt and pepper after removing from grill.

title: louisiana pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl. In a large bowl, beat butter, eggs, vanilla and cream until well blended. Add pecans and dry ingredients to this. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender at once and blend until mixed.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: milk gravy
directions: In saucepan, heat oil or drippings until hot. Add flour and stir constantly until browning begins. Pour canned milk slowly into saucepan while stirring; reduce heat to medium. Stir constantly to get all lumps out. May need to add a little sweet milk to keep gravy from being too thick. Just keep stirring and adding milk slowly to reach right consistency. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir together by hand (do not use mixer) all ingredients, adding nuts and apples last.
Sprinkle top with 6 ounce package of butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour, butter, soup and water. Mix well.
Form patties and roll in flour.
Brown both sides in butter.
Pour soup and water over steaks and simmer covered for 45 minutes.
Turn after 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off top of each pepper. Remove seeds. Parboil in boiling water in saucepan for 3 to 4 minutes and drain.
Brown turkey with onion in skillet coated with Pam cooking spray. Add tomatoes. Simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Mix well. Stuff green peppers with turkey mixture. Place in shallow baking dish. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well for easy spreading. Makes enough salad for 4 sandwiches.

title: jamaican curried chicken
directions: Dice raw chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Add all seasonings, except curry powder.
Using a spoon, add the curry powder to the mixture until the meat is colored yellow.
Allow to rest in refrigerator overnight to improve the flavor of the curry.
Heat Dutch oven pot after spraying with pan spray.
Add meat to pot; cover and lower heat on stove to medium level.
Stir meat occasionally to distribute seasonings.
When meat is cooked, mix water and cornstarch and add to curry to thicken up the meat juices and make a gravy.
Turn heat on stove to low and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve with steamed white rice and mixed vegetables.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat Jell-O and strawberries
or raspberries until dissolved. Cool. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Put in a 9-inch pan. Refrigerate.
(Double for a 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening, vegetable oil and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and sour milk.
Mix until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Mix in zucchini last.
Spoon into pan and sprinkle top of cake with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Layer cucumber slices and salt in medium bowl.
Chill about 1 hour.
Drain; squeeze dry.
Blend the sour cream, vinegar and sugar; fold into cucumbers.
Serve with black pepper.

title: pickle in a jar
directions: Cut cucumbers across in round the thickness desired.
Fill a quart jar with the cucumber slices.
Cover cucumbers with apple vinegar and put a screw-on lid on the jar tight.
Put aside for several or more months.
Pour off the vinegar (the cucumbers will have shrunk to about half volume).
Fill a jar with cucumbers, leaving an inch or so at the top.
Cover the cucumbers with as much sugar as the jar will take.

title: harvard beets
directions: In double boiler, blend 2 tablespoons cornstarch with orange juice and lemon until smooth.
Place over heat and stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup sugar and oleo, rinds, salt and pepper.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Blend well. Stir in beets and heat over low heat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces and brown.
Remove and add celery, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute vegetables, then return meat to pan and add tomato soup, wine, carrots and mushrooms.
Simmer until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries in a food processor or blender.
Cut apples into small pieces (leave peel on).
Peel oranges and cut into small pieces.
Place the fruit into a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and jello (do not add water to jello!).
Add crushed pineapple and mix well.
Refrigerate a couple of hours before serving.

title: sour cream freeze
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a mold and freeze.
This is great with turkey and dressing.

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer in large salad bowl all preceding ingredients in the order they are written.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: blueberry cream cheese cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Makes 2 layers. Each layer, make into 2 layers.
Both will make 4 thinner layers.

title: cranberry pecan muffins
directions: Combine cranberries and 1/4 cup sugar, set aside.
Combine flour, cup of sugar and baking powder, mix well.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
This can be done in food processor.
Stir in pecans.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in milk. Add to dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened.
Gently stir in cranberry mixture. Spoon batter in muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Yield: 24 cupcakes.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: **1/2 c. fat free egg substitute can be used instead of egg whites. Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, and cinnamon in a medium sized bowl and stir to mix well. Stir in the pineapple, including the juice, milk, egg whites or egg substitute and vanilla. Fold in carrots, raisins, and if desired pecans. Coat a 9 x 13 inch pan with non-stick cooking spray. Spread the batter evenly in the pan and bake at 325° for 35 minutes, or just until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of cake comes out clean. Cool to room temperature.

title: quick borsch(russian beet soup)
directions: Heat broth, beets with liquid from can, cabbage, onion and sugar to boiling point.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and refrigerate.
At time of serving, either serve hot or cold; top with spoonful of sour cream.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: grandma's date pudding
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients in a good rolling boil.
While this is boiling, mix remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls in 9 x 12-inch pan, spreading when mixture is all in pan.
Pour syrup over this batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer potatoes and onions on top.
Mix tomatoes and sour cream in blender.
Pour over chops, potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate mayo-cake
directions: Dissolve soda in water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add water, vanilla and mayo.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup of corn flakes.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add a little chicken broth if needed.
Top with the other 1/2 cup of corn flakes.
Bake in oven 1 hour or in microwave for 20 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.

title: chocolate walnut sensations
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In
a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a larger mixing bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in egg. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate morsels and chopped walnuts.
Spread into a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake 23 to 25 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle remaining 2/3 cup chocolate morsels over top.
Let stand until morsels become shiny and soft.
Spread chocolate evenly over top. Garnish with walnut halves. When cool (chill 5 to 10 minutes to set chocolate), cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes about 24 bars.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cake layers in bottom of a punch bowl.
Add one layer of each ingredient.
Repeat until completed.
Add Cool Whip on top and cover with coconut.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix flour and water into a thin paste.
Cut strips of newspaper and soak in mixture.
Place wet strips around a balloon or ball of newspaper.
Let dry overnight.
Decorate the next day.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chopped chicken and celery in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour broth and chicken soup over this. Add salt and pepper.
Mix softened butter, flour and milk together and pour over previous mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Line bottom of pan with graham crackers.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Set aside.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, leaving out 1/2 cup milk.
Add cream cheese mixture to pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour over graham crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers over pudding mixture.
In separate bowl, melt chocolate chips with rest of margarine.
Mix well.
Add confectioners sugar.
Pour on top of crackers.
Add water if needed to thin mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: black-eyed susan cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pans with foil cupcake cups, 2-inches in diameter.
Place one vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Spoon heaping tablespoonfuls of cream cheese mixture into each cup.
Bake 15 minutes, or until set, but not browned.
Cool in pans.
In small microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips and butter.
Microwave on High 30 seconds to 1 minute or until melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
Drop teaspoonfuls of chocolate mixture onto center of each cheesecake.
Place almond slices around dab of chocolate to resemble petals.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: fiesta fudge
directions: Combine in a heavy 3-quart saucepan the sugar, margarine, milk and salt. Bring to a full rolling boil over high heat, stirring. Remove from heat. Stir until melted the creamy peanut butter.
Add and stir until blended the vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Fold in the M&M's candies.
Spread in greased 9 x 15-inch pan. Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Place veggies in layers around meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer to brown meat.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: oh so gooie brownies(yield one 9 x 9-inch pan)
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour. Pour in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Serve hot.

title: deep dish chicken-vegetable pie
directions: Place vegetables in a boiler and add chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in half and half and poultry seasoning.
In a small bowl mix margarine and flour into a paste.
Drop lump of paste into sauce. Stir over low heat until flour paste melts and sauce thickens. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper.
Cut chicken into large pieces.
Stir chicken into sauce.
Pour mixture into 2 or 3-quart casserole.
Place crust over filling all the way to the edge of casserole dish.
Prick top to allow steam to escape.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: diabetic lemon pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Separate eggs, placing whites in large bowl.
With electric mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.
Add lemon peel and juice to egg yolks; with same beater at medium speed, beat until well blended. Add milk; beat at low speed 1 minute.
Add sweetener, flour and salt.
Beat at low speed just until smooth.
Fold into egg whites. Turn into 6 custard cups.
Place in baking pan.
Pour water to 1 inch depth around cups.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly brown on top.
Serve warm or cold.

title: applesauce cookies(drop cookie)
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Stir in coffee and applesauce. Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting. Mix remaining ingredients; stir into applesauce mixture. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: cheryl's pie crust
directions: In large bowl, cut lard and salt into flour until pea size balls form.
Combine milk, vinegar and beaten egg; mix and add to flour mixture.
Stir few times to form ball or will stick together.
Take handful and form ball.
Roll out.
Makes 5 crusts.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together and chill 2 hours.
Roll into balls.
Freeze or cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup milk and melted butter.
Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: red-jacket potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook in boiling water to cover with 1/2 teaspoon salt for 10 minutes, or until tender.
Set aside. Combine mayonnaise and the next 6 ingredients.
Combine potatoes, eggs and mayonnaise mixture, tossing gently.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired; sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 6 servings.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese together until cheese is melted. Mix water and gelatine together and add to soup mixture. Cover and let cool. Blend all other ingredients and add to soup mixture. Grease gelatine mold with salad dressing (Miracle Whip). Fill with ingredients. Refrigerate at least 6 hours. Remove from gelatine mold and serve with crackers.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco, add eggs, milk, soda and tartar.
Blend together, then add flour.
Roll out on floured board and cut with water glass.
Put one on bottom.
Add filling and put one on top. Cut slit in top cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: krispy klusters
directions: Melt chocolate bark in bowl in microwave (or double boiler). When well melted, mix in peanuts and Rice Krispies and mix well. With teaspoon, drop spoon sizes on waxed paper.
Allow about one inch between each, then let cool.
May be placed in candy-sized paper cups.
Makes 70 to 75 pieces.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti noodles as directed.
Combine hot noodles with Cheez Whiz and soup.
Mix well.
Add chicken.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: "mother" bolander's potato soup with vegetables
directions: Cook 10 minutes in pressure cooker or until tender in a large kettle.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender; stir in flour. Gradually stir in water, broccoli, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and broccoli is tender (about 10 minutes).
Add cheese and half and half.
Cook until smooth and creamy.
Do not boil.

title: tropical muffins(diabetic)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar substitute, baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl; stir in coconut and make a well in center of mixture.
Combine bananas, margarine, egg, orange rind and juice; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking powder and salt.
Add to the other mixture and stir.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll into mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients together and mix well. Bake in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon braised pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in heavy skillet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Top each pork chop with a thin slice of lemon.
Make a sauce with the remaining ingredients.
Heat sauce until steaming.
Pour sauce over chops; cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: unbaked date cookies
directions: Cook dates, egg, butter and brown sugar in a heavy frying pan over low heat until thick, like marmalade.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Cool.
Butter hands and roll mixture into balls.
The balls may be rolled in powdered or granulated sugar.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp cullen
directions: Wrap 1 shrimp around 1 water chestnut; wrap in 1 bacon piece and secure with toothpick. Repeat with remaining 23. Melt 3 Tbsp. butter in heavy skillet over high heat. Add half of shrimp and cook until bacon browns, about 2 1/2 minutes per side. Transfer to large au gratin dish. Repeat with remaining butter and shrimp. Preheat broiler. Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth. Blend remaining ingredients. Spoon sauce over shrimp. Broil until top is golden brown. Divide and enjoy.

title: divinity puff
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to thin syrup stage. Slowly pour 1/3 syrup over egg whites, beating constantly. Cook remaining syrup to thread stage. Add 1/2 to egg whites, beating constantly. Cook remaining syrup to stiff firm ball and add to egg mixture. Add vanilla and continue beating until mixture holds shape when dropped from spoon on waxed paper.

title: apricot bars(temp:  350~.  time:  55 minutes.  yield:  32)
directions: Rinse apricots; cover with water and boil 10 minutes.
Drain; cool and chop.
Heat oven.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix, until crumbly, butter, granulated sugar and 1 cup flour.
Pack into pan. Bake about 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Sift together 1/3 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually beat brown sugar into eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Mix in vanilla, nuts and apricots.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake 20 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pan; roll in confectioners sugar.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix Knox gelatine and jello together. Add boiling water.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Cut in squares.

title: black joe cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs till creamed. Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and mix. Make into balls and roll in cinnamon sugar mixture. Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add 10 egg yolks; beat.
Then add 10 egg whites.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Grease and flour angel food pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb apple crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb or apples, sugar, 6 tablespoons flour and cinnamon together and put into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut together oats, brown sugar, 1 1/2 cups flour, butter or margarine and shortening and crumble over first mixture.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter.
Saute next 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add and simmer 5 minutes. Add salt, pepper and cayenne to taste and simmer 15 more minutes. Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 6.

title: low calorie swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook onions in margarine until golden.
Make meatballs.
Remove onions and cook meatballs. Remove meatballs.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Stir together in a bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of the flour mixture.
In another bowl, beat eggs; stir in milk and oil.
Pour egg mixture into flour mixture. Stir just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be slightly lumpy. Do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full of batter.
Drop a little jelly in center of batter.
Add more batter to fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to the package directions.
Stew and cut up chicken.
In a separate bowl mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Alternate layers of chicken, broccoli and soup in casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in bowl.
Add flour, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon of salt; mix well.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Shape into pretzels on baking sheet.
Brush with egg.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: grand quiche
directions: Place cheese slices in pie shell.
Sprinkle with crabmeat, shrimp, mushrooms, pepper, onion and celery.
In a bowl, mix the eggs, half and half, soup, garlic powder, Tabasco and flour; pour into shell.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spray 2-quart oblong baking dish with vegetable cooking spray. Arrange chicken, bone side down, in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and black pepper.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: potato dumplings - norwegian kamler
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Drain off surplus water, important not to be too wet.
Add salt and knead in enough flour to thicken. Boil in salted water for about an hour.

title: turkey and rice
directions: *I use L'eggs but can use any other seasoning.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix sour cream with mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Mix avocados with lemon and 2 tablespoons finely chopped onion.
Layer on pizza pan or 2 plates the bean dip, chopped green chilies, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, 4 ounces cheese, tomatoes, green onions, black olives and 4 ounces grated cheese.
Garnish with some chopped tomato, green onion and black olive.

title: new england fried clams
directions: Combine ingredients except for clams and egg whites. Refrigerate batter for 3 to 12 hours if possible, if not, mix batter as little as possible.
It should not run off a large spoon in a ribbon but should fall off in pieces.
Then, fold in egg whites if desired.
Drain clams; dry them.
Retain clam juice for soup.
Peel the neck from clams and pour the batter over them, making sure they are well covered.
Drop whole clams one by one into hot fat and fry until a light brown.
Batter is enough for 1 1/2 cups of clams.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Spoon in 1 pie crust. Cover with other pie crust. Split top of crust and brush with egg. Bake until both crusts are brown at 375° (approximately 40 minutes). Allow to cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: First prepare topping mixture by rubbing together 2 tablespoons of fat, 2 tablespoons flour, 1/3 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/3 cup sugar and chopped nuts, if available.
Next, rub 2 tablespoons fat into 2 cups flour.
Beat together egg, 3 tablespoons sugar and milk.
Combine with flour by stirring until smooth for about 1/2 minute.
Then beat vigorously for 1/2 minute. Spread in a lightly greased 8 x 8-inch deep pan.
Finally sprinkle topping mixture on cake batter and bake in hot oven at 400° for 22 minutes.

title: granny clyde's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, yellow Crisco, sugar and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add alternately the flour and milk.
Add in other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bean and macaroni soup(servings:  16)
directions: Drain beans and reserve liquid.
Rinse beans.
Heat oil in a 6-quart kettle; add mushrooms, onion, carrot, celery and garlic and saute 5 minutes.
Add tomato, sage, thyme, oregano, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover and cook over medium heat 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package.
Drain when cooked.
Do not overcook.
Add beans and reserved bean liquid (add water to make 4 cups) and cooked macaroni.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until soup is heated.
Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Crumble cookies and add 1 1/2 to 2 cups in cake mix, leave enough to add to icing.
Bake according to cake mix directions.

title: marsha arant's homemade hush puppies
directions: Mix together and deep fry!

title: play dough (cooked)
directions: Cook 3 minutes to consistency of mashed potatoes.
Knead a bit.
Store in plastic bag or airtight container.
(Not edible.)

title: quaker natural chocolate chippers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in cereal, oats and chocolate pieces. Drop by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store, tightly covered.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and very little juice.
Pour mixture into an oiled Bundt pan.
When Jell-O is set, beat together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on Jell-O.
Mix together pretzels, sugar and butter.
Sprinkle on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until set.
Unmold to serve. Can be served as a dessert.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Add enough Pet milk to mix.
Spread on cake.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta al dente (do not overcook pasta).
Drain, rinse and put into a large mixing bowl with oil and garlic.
Mix well.
Cook beans and carrots al dente.
When beans and carrots are 50% cooked, add peas and onions and continue cooking until vegetables are cooked al dente; do not overcook vegetables.
Drain vegetables and add to pasta with vinegar and sour cream.
Mix gently, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Add cayenne pepper if desired. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: hot spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 45 min. covered. Then, uncover and simmer 45 more min. Add water as needed.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Drain small pieces of fat from broth. Dice lean meat or simmer ground beef in 2 cups of water for 15 minutes. Add tomato or juice, paprika and sugar to broth and meat. Cook potatoes, carrots, onions and peas until tender. Cook noodles in water and drain. Add all vegetables and noodles to broth and simmer for 30 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste. Leftover vegetables are fine to use in this soup.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with milk until creamy.
Add onion, horseradish and crab meat.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until heated.
Serve as a spread on rye bread.

title: nine day pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers.
Place in a crock or stainless steel container.
Cover cucumbers with a brine made with water and salt. (If amount is increased, keep proportions the same.)
Let stand one week.
Drain.
Cover cucumbers with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain again.
Dissolve alum in enough boiling water to cover the cukes.
Let stand 24 hours.
Cut each pickle into bite size pieces and place in sterilized jars.
Cook together until seasoned the vinegar, sugar and spices.
Pour this syrup over the pickles in the jars.
Seal.
Best sweet pickle I've ever tasted.

title: slice of lemon pie
directions: Beat together the first 5 ingredients.
Add rind, lemon and water and blend well.
Turn into pastry-lined 8-inch pie tin and cover with pastry, sealing edges.
Make air vents in top crust. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix.
Mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of cookie crumbs.
Top with remaining cookie crumbs.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Combine thoroughly and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

Place 2 tortillas, side by side, in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top each tortilla with some meat mixture and grated cheese. Repeat until each stack contains 6 tortillas layered with meat and cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is bubbly. Cut each torte (stack) into quarters with a sharp knife before serving.

title: barbecued sauerkraut
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in an uncovered baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: date fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with Pam or Baker's Joy.
In a mixing bowl, with a fork or whisk, blend oatmeal, Vita Fiber, baking soda, cinnamon, raisins and dates.
In a small bowl, combine milk and honey.
Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Slowly, about 1/4 cup at a time, add the sugar to the whites and continue to beat until stiff and glossy.

title: anise drops
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together; set aside.
Combine eggs and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat for 30 minutes on medium speed.
Add flour; blend thoroughly.
Beat for 3 additional minutes.
Add anise flavoring to taste.
Drop cookies from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Let stand overnight in a cool, dry place.
Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes.
Cookies should form a creamy white "cap".
Makes 8 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: rice salad with mushrooms
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt and butter and using bouillon cubes instead.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: supreme cheesecake
directions: For crust, combine 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon peel.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add 1 beaten egg yolk and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Pat 1/2 of dough on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan (sides removed).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Butter sides of pan; attach to bottom.
Pat remaining dough around side of pan.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook onions and garlic in pan with Wesson oil.
Have the hamburger all ready cooked.
When onions are soft, add hamburger. Mix in all other ingredients.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add water or tomato juice if needed.
Cooks well in crock-pot.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Tear apart the angel food cake into large bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, combine the cream cheese, milk and vanilla pudding.
Whisk until smooth. Pour this creamed mixture over the cake pieces.
Spread the thawed strawberries on top of creamed mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over entire top of dish.
Chill before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or in crock-pot 1 hour on high, then reduce to low and bake 6 to 8 hours.

title: honey peanut butter brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together the sugar, corn oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf or 3 smaller loaves.

title: imitation girl scout mint cookies
directions: Melt chocolate discs; add peppermint extract to melted chocolate.
Dip Ritz crackers into the melted chocolate and let cool so chocolate gets firm.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well, chill and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: grammie wing's brown bread
directions: Mix well, grease container and fill half full, place and cover them and steam for 3 hours.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Pour into small unbaked shells.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 small pies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide into greased, floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until center test done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the oleo and stuffing mix.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: turkey reubens
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl; toss well and set aside.
Spread mustard evenly over 6 bread slices and top with turkey.
Top each with 1 cheese slice and 1/4 cup cabbage mixture. Top with remaining bread slices.
Spray both slices of each sandwich with cooking spray; place on a hot griddle or skillet coated with cooking spray.
Cook 2 minutes on each side or until bread is lightly browned and cheese melts.
Serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind the frozen Oreos until they look like dirt. In big bowl, soften cream cheese. Add pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Beat until smooth. In a 9 x 12 pan, layer dirt, pudding, dirt, pudding, then dirt on top. Chill thoroughly.

title: no bake peanut cookies
directions: Combine sugar, salt, milk and syrup in a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Stir occasionally and cook until soft ball stage (236°) or until syrup dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir until blended.
Stir in oats and peanuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: shepherd pie casserole
directions: Brown meat and place in greased casserole dish. Place greenbeans over meat. Mix soup with the milk; then pour over beans. Place tater tots over entire mixture. Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: banana cake with quick caramel frosting
directions: Place rack in center of oven and preheat to 350°. Lightly grease 2 (9-inch) pans with solid vegetable shortening, then dust with flour. Shake out excess flour and set the pans aside. Mix dry cake mix, brown sugar and cinnamon in large mixing bowl. Add mashed bananas, water, oil and eggs. Blend with electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute. Stop the mixer and scrape down the sides of the bowl with a rubber spatula. Increase mixer speed to medium and beat for 2 minutes, scraping down the sides again if needed. The batter should look well blended and the bananas should be well pureed.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: Prepare rice and set off to the side to allow to cool.
Brown beef, garlic and ginger; drain.
Heat vegetable oil over medium heat until hot.
Stir-fry pepper and pea pods 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add rice, soy sauce and sesame oil; mix well. Return beef and heat 5 minutes.
Stir in green onion.
You can put any kind of meat in place of the beef.

title: sausage and mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pie shells and bake 8 minutes. In large skillet, brown sausage, breaking into pieces.
Remove sausage from drippings and add drained mushrooms and onion.
Cook and stir 5 minutes; drain.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and mix with 2 cups sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, drain off the juice.
Mix drained cranberries, grapes and nuts into the Cool Whip.

title: harvest loaf cake(pumpkin cake)
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Cream well.
Blend in eggs; beat well.
At low speed, add pumpkin alternately with dry ingredients, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate bits and 1/2 cup walnuts. Grease bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Pour in mixture; sprinkle 1/4 cup walnuts over.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Cool and drizzle with glaze.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; do not overcook. Place in 2-quart dish. Combine soup, egg, milk and mayonnaise. Mix well. Add cheese. Mix well. Pour over broccoli and toss. Mix margarine and herb season stuffing. Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and beat eggs well.
Add bananas and lemon juice.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts. Pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruited punch
directions: Stir pineapple juice into concentrates.
Add 2 quarts water; mix well.
Chill.
To serve slowly pour in 7-Up.
Garnish with slices of oranges, lemons and limes.
Makes 28 cups.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes about two cups.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except peanuts, corn and soda.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Pour over corn and peanuts; stir well.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.
After cooled, store in airtight container. Keeps well.

title: tomato beef casserole
directions: Fry together hamburger, celery, onion, green pepper and season with salt and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Place this mixture in a casserole and arrange the biscuits on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 8.

title: french chicken rolls(children's)
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Pound with meat mallet until thin.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese on each chicken breast and roll up; fasten with wooden toothpicks. Dip into the egg white, then roll in bread crumbs.
Pour half the butter into a baking dish.
Arrange chicken rolls in the butter. Pour the rest of the butter over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot caramel apples
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Saute apples about 5 minutes, turning frequently.
Add sugar, cinnamon and brandy to apples and place in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in an uncovered baking dish. Serve hot or cold.

title: buffet vegetable bake
directions: Toss vegetables with cheese in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour melted butter over vegetables.
Add salt to sauce and pour over vegetables.
Mix. Bake at 325° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet peach pickles
directions: Select firm clingstone peaches.
Remove the skin; tie spices in muslin bag and boil syrup of sugar and vinegar several minutes. Drop in a few peaches at a time and when tender, put in hot sterilized jars and pour syrup over them.

title: strawberry pineapple salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and honey in a bowl.
Add strawberries and pineapple; blend well.
Pour into a freezer tray and freeze 2 hours.
Cut into 4 portions.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with strawberry slices if desired.
Add nuts if desired.

title: meat marinade(for pork tenderloin)
directions: Pour over meat. Let stand 1/2 hour at room temperature or 2 hours in the refrigerator. Bake at 350 degrees until meat thermometer reaches 160 degrees. Continue cooking for 10 more minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together, add enough water to make 2 gallons.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix 3 cups flour with the other ingredients well. Mix in the other 3 cups flour slowly. Mix well. Put into greased bowl and turn greased side up. Let rise 1 hour in warm place. Knead well. Make into rolls and let rise another hour. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until done.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cool and cut into bite-size pieces. Cook rice in chicken broth.
Pack cooked rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 4 to 5 teaspoons of broth on top. Place chopped chicken on top of rice.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with butter.
Spread on top of casserole.
Sprinkle top with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: robin's hot chicken dip
directions: Toast almonds.
Mix all ingredients.
Heat and serve on crackers.
Double the recipe for parties.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and stir often for 3 hours.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside. Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy, set aside.
Combine milk, pudding and Cool Whip. Beat into cream cheese mixture until smooth.
Layer pudding and Oreos.
Top layer should be Oreo cookies.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Bring to boil, stirring continuously.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: brownies
directions: Mix and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
(May not bake done.)

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Bake at 275°.
Stir when half done.
Keep covered while cooking.

title: maple flavored fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, corn syrup, milk and maple flavoring in large, heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat for about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add nuts and coconut; increase heat.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus on bottom of buttered casserole dish, then egg slices and cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Combine soup and seasonings and pour over asparagus mixture.
Dot with butter and bake at 300° for about 25 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and run into oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Pack into a greased
9	x
5-inch
pan and shape.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with cheese.
Return to oven with cheese melts.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Follow cake mix recipe.
Put aside.
Pour melted butter in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Add sugar, press all around with spoon.
Put pineapple slices all around, flat, usually 6 will work.
Add 1 cherry in middle of each pineapple.
Gently pour cake mix over top.
Put in oven at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip 3
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of a microwave-safe dish. Spread a layer of chili over the cream cheese. Finish with a layer of shredded Cheddar cheese. Microwave for 5 minutes or until the cheese melts. Serve with spicy nacho tortilla chips.

title: great cabbage soup
directions: Pour oil in stock pot over low heat.
Add onion and garlic. Cook 5 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup chicken broth and heat 5 minutes; stirring occasionally.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 40 minutes.
Serve with bread.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fancy oyster crackers
directions: Mix first 5 items.
Pour over crackers, which have been placed in a Tupperware container with top.

title: no-cook taco bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a large plate.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning and spread over layer of beans.
Add a layer of diced tomatoes, then a layer of diced green onions.
Top with shredded cheese.
I put this in the microwave just to barely melt cheese.
Olives, chopped jalapenos, etc. can be added.
Serve with corn chips.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Beat together milk, pudding mixes and vanilla.
Combine these two mixtures.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: hot tuna burgers
directions: Form in patties.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve with or without buns.

title: chew bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix ingredients in the order listed and pour into prepared pan. Check after 20 minutes of baking.
Do not overbake.
If it seems a little gooey in the middle, it will finish cooking once you take it out of the oven.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix and press the first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Beat milk and peanut butter at medium speed until creamy. Add baking mix and vanilla, beating at low speed until blended.

title: we 3 peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and make rounded teaspoons into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork dipped in sugar. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool before serving.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Heat milk until warm, then stir in flour.
Continue to cook until mixture becomes as thick as paste, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and let cool to touch.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; when paste is cool, add and continue to beat until fluffy.
Enjoy.

title: super chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in large baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Combine stuffing mix and chicken broth in bowl.
Spread over soup and sour cream mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, milk and soda in a large boiler to a "soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter, Karo and vanilla. Stir well to mix.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper that has been sprinkled with salt. They will harden rapidly.
When cool, place in your favorite candy dish to look and taste delightful.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs, flour, soda, sour cream, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix in separate bowl brown sugar, nuts, melted oleo and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Put in rest of batter and put rest of crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: carrot-apple salad
directions: Lightly coat ingredients with mayonnaise. Can substitute pineapple instead of apples.

title: christmas tree cookies
directions: In large saucepan heat butter and marshmallows over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and food color.
Fold in cereal until evenly coated.

On waxed paper, quickly shape warm mixture with buttered hands into Christmas tree shapes, using about 2/3 cup mixture for each place-card size tree or 1/4 cup mixture for each individual cookie size tree.

title: just heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly grease bottom of 9x13x2 inch baking pan.
Make cake according to directions on box of cake mix.
Combine cream of coconut and thawed coconut.
Mix well.
As soon as cake comes from oven, make holes in cake using fork.
Pour coconut mixture over top.
Beat cream cheese until softened and smooth.
Combine chocolate milk and chocolate pudding mix. Whisk until smooth. Add to cream cheese and beat until well blended. Spoon this mixture over top of coconut.
Top with Cool Whip.
If desired, sprinkle toasted pecans over top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: beef kabobs waikiki
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients except meat and vegetables. Stir until well blended.
Place cubed meat in a 9
x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour marinade over and refrigerate overnight.
Turn occasionally.

title: potatoes and chicken casserole
directions: Slice larger potatoes into single layer until bottom of casserole dish is covered.
Slice onion and layer over potatoes. Add chopped chicken and cheese, then add another layer of potatoes.
Add cans of soup; spread evenly across the top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°; cover with foil.
When potatoes are tender, casserole is done.

title: sunny day punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with orange slices and scoops of sherbet.

title: hotdog chili sauce
directions: In sauce pan add ground beef, water and salt.
Cook until tender but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, honey, peanut butter and margarine in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Add vanilla, cornflakes, oatmeal and coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate chewy critters
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Add the milk and vanilla, then stir in the flour and salt.
On an ungreased cookie sheet, arrange 4 pecan halves at right angles to one another.
Divide the dough into 30 equal parts.
Form each piece of dough around a piece of caramel, covering the candy completely.
Press each one firmly on a cluster of pecan halves. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until firm.
Cool completely on a rack.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; stir in egg. Mix dry ingredients together. Blend in. Add vanilla and stir well. Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (until they rise and sort of crack). Cut while warm.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix gelatin with 2 cups boiling water; add pineapple and 7-Up. Place in large baking dish.
Place marshmallows over gelatin. Mix Dream Whip, cheese, milk and vanilla; whip together.
Spread over marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: cheerios treats(preparation time:  5 minutes, plus cooling.)
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine in a large microwave bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows.
Toss to coat with margarine.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately add cereal.
Mix lightly until well coated. Press mixture into prepared pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes about 24.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, milk, eggs and corn in a mixing bowl. Blend well and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Set aside.
Pour 1/2 of corn meal batter into a greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumble beef over cheese. Sprinkle with onion and peppers.
Pour remaining corn meal over top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: new orleans red beans
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight or from 4 to 6 hours.
Pour off water and refill pot with water, allowing plenty of room to simmer. Add ham bone and ham and all other ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 3 hours or until creamy (water may added if necessary).
Large sausage, sliced in 1-inch lengths may be added the last hour. (Should be thick and creamy.)
Serve over fluffy rice.
This is a typical New Orleans lunch dish.
Leftover beans may be frozen for future use.

title: squirrel stroganoff
directions: Saute onion until tender.
Stir in the meat, add garlic and cook until golden.
Lay noodles over the squirrel and onion.
Mix tomato sauce with 1 cup water, wine, mushrooms, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour this over the noodles and meat. Bring to a boil and simmer until the noodles are soft.
Stir in the sour cream and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over cereal in a large container.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Be careful when you mix.
Don't use a spoon; it will make the cereal crumble.
Works best if you have a large container with lid so you can shake it until coated.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Blend and beat together the zest, sugar, butter and egg. Add the flour, baking powder and lemon juice. Blend well. Divide the mixture into 2 portions. On foil, form each into a long cylinder. Wrap and chill for several hours. When ready to bake, roll the dough in sugar and slice 1/4-inch thick. Place on buttered baking sheets, leaving room between each cookie. Top with a pecan half and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: open-face broccoli sandwich
directions: Steam enough broccoli to cover a piece of bread; cook to desired tenderness (not mushy).
Toast a slice of bread, then butter it, placing toast on cookie sheet or small pan.
Place cooked broccoli on top of toast and salt it.
Top with sliced or grated cheese, not more than 1/4 inch thick.
Put in oven or toaster oven until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate the cheese.
Mix all ingredients together by hand, adding Bisquick until good, but not too, dry consistency.
Make 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet (I line it with foil).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 65.
Serve warm.

title: lasagna(microwave)
directions: Brown ground beef in large pan.
You may add some minced onions if you like.
Drain and stir in salt, spaghetti sauce mix and tomato juice; mix well.

title: pure sin cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 1/2 evaporated milk and bake as box directs until firm, using two 8-inch rounds.
Meanwhile, melt caramels with remaining milk.
On first layer of cake, layer with melted caramels, nuts and chocolate chips.
Top with second layer.
Place the Hershey bars on top of cake and bake until melted.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside. In a large mixing bowl, whisk together applesauce, sugar, egg whites, bananas and vanilla.
Add flour mixture all at once and stir gently to blend.
Pour batter into prepared loaf pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool bread completely before slicing.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Put foil-lined muffin papers in muffin tins.
Place a cookie in each cup.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix turkey, eggs, onion soup mix, oatmeal and 2/3 of the ketchup.
Put in greased pan.
Poke
8 holes in the top.
Cover with remaining ketchup.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Let set 10 minutes before slicing.

title: very easy pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Cover with water and 2 cups salt.
Add 1 tray of ice cubes and soak overnight.
Mix remaining ingredients the next day and bring liquid to boil.
Slice small onions (amount to taste) and put into the mixture to boil.
Add cucumber slices (drained) and boil 4 minutes.
Pour into jars and refrigerate.

title: favorite bread recipe
directions: Warm
water
in
pan.
Add all other ingredients except flour. Measure flour into extra large bowl or pan.
Add water mixture to flour all at
once.
Stir
and mix with spoon until too stiff. Begin kneading and knead until dough is smooth and elastic, adding more flour if needed.
Grease extra large bowl or pan and place dough
in
bowl
or
pan.
Cover and let rise until double. Punch down and let rise again. Shape into loaves and place into pans. Makes
6 to 8 loaves.
Let rise again in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This bread is great.

title: aglio e olio(pasta with garlic and oil)
directions: Heat oil in saucepan over low heat.
Gently saute garlic until golden brown.
Add anchovies and stir.
Cook pasta al dente; pour into large serving bowl.
Toss with garlic and oil mixture.
Add parsley and basil.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve immediately. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes; cut each potato in half lengthwise, then cut in wedges. Boil 5 minutes with salt.
Drain and dry.
Layer potatoes on lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend butter with grated cheese until smooth, add Worcestershire sauce. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the mixture, add pecans, mix thoroughly. Shape into a roll about 1-1/2 inches in diameter and wrap in waxed paper. Chill, slice thin and bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: burger king whopper
directions: Take Cattle Scales Road down to Route 827, then to Route 254. Turn left and head into Waynesboro. When you get to the stop light, stop (if red).
Continue on 254 to King Avenue.
Stop by the 7-11 for a Slurpee.
Go down King Avenue to Broad Street and turn right.
Turn right into Burger King and ask the lovely lady for a Whopper.
Pay her. Go home.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Beat egg whites very stiff.
Put on pie and brown.

title: deviled egg sandwiches
directions: Put egg through meat grinder.
Add other ingredients; mix well.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form. Beat in nuts, cracker crumbs and vanilla. Spoon into 9-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool. Stir nuts into Cool Whip. Spread over cool pie before serving. Put Cool Whip on top to serve.
