title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and blackberry jam, beating thoroughly.
Sift flour; measure and resift with soda and spices.
Add alternately with buttermilk, beating well each time. Stir in nuts to distribute evenly; pour into well greased tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 55 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: crock-pot baked ham
directions: Clean ham and while still damp, rub ham in honey.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour Pepsi over ham.
Cook on high for 15 minutes, then reduce heat and cook until done.
(Could simmer for up to 8 hours.)

title: chicken grilled on charcoal salad(servings:  4)
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper, garlic and rosemary.
Let stand for approximately 1 hour.
Grill on charcoal until brown. Cut vegetables into bite-size.
Chill.
Mix olive oil, wine vinegar, soy sauce, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Serve cool.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese; add other ingredients and mix well.
Shape in a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and chill.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Roll out crescent rolls onto 1 large (or 2 small) cookie sheets.
Seal off perforations.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes (lightly brown).
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper and onion.
Saute a little; add tomato sauce and simmer.
Mix soft cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream together.
Layer 1/2 noodles first, then cheese mixture, 1/2 noodles, then hamburger mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudgsicles
directions: In a saucepan, heat the sugar, 1/3 cup milk, egg, salt and chocolate chips until the chips are melted.
Remove from the heat and add the other 1/3 cup milk and the vanilla.
Pour into molds and freeze.

title: sister bessie's rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, Crisco, sugar and salt until warm.
Stir to melt Crisco. Add to dry ingredients; add egg and beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour and mix with hand.
Place in a greased bowl; let rise for 1 1/2 hours and then knead and roll out.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; melt Crisco.
Add onions and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Add cooked noodles and tuna; stir in grated cheese.
Place in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over medium heat; add peanuts and continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently. Cook until peanuts are completely sugar coated and no syrup remains (about 30 minutes).
Pour out onto ungreased cookie sheet; separate peanuts with fork.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Stir at 10 minute intervals.
Makes 1 pound.

title: blueberry-sour cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sour cream, sugar, flour, egg, almond extract and salt into a bowl.
Mix in blueberries. Spoon into crust. Bake until filling is set, approximately 25 minutes.

title: 4 calories soup
directions: Cook in large pot for 30 to 45 minutes, then serve.
This contains only 4 calories per serving.

title: cheesy tortilla corn
directions: Cook and stir onion and red pepper in 2 tablespoons of the margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat until tender. Reduce heat to low.
Stir in corn and Velveeta cheese.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until Velveeta is melted and mixture is thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons margarine in separate pan.
Stir in tortilla chips and seasoning. Cook over medium heat 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.

title: syrup cake
directions: Cream
butter
until
soft.
Add
sugar and blend well. Add eggs
and
mix.
Add
milk, syrup, flour, soda and spices; mix until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan which has been lined with greased waxed paper.

title: south of the border lasagne
directions: Spray bottom of glass 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, taco seasoning and chilies.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Heat beans.
Layer tortillas on bottom of pan.
Cover with refried beans, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: crescent apple quicks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine apple, pecans, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; stir until apple is well coated. Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon apple mixture onto center of each triangle.
Fold 3 points of dough over filling, overlapping, like an envelope; press gently.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 23 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Mix creamed butter and shortening until smooth.
Add sugar, vanilla, lemon extract and lemon juice.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.

title: mickey mouse salad
directions: Place lettuce leaves on plate with half a pear, round side up, in center.
Use pecans for ears, raisins for eyes and cherry for nose.
If cream cheese or cottage cheese is favorite, fill in the pear cavity for another surprise.

title: marshmallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate pieces and peanut butter over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Pour in marshmallows, then pour into 9-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: buffalo chili in a bread bowl
directions: Let bread dough thaw, cut in half giving you two.
Spray 2 large soup bowls with nonstick spray on bottom side and form dough over bowl.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw broccoli. Mix all ingredients together. Bake approximately 1 hour in large baking dish.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, milk, onion and seasonings.
Form into 4 balls.
Fry in melted shortening, turning so as to brown lightly, but not get crusty.
Add sauces and water.
Mix well.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes over low heat.
Add a small amount of water, if liquid cooks down too much.
Makes 2 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Pour Worcestershire sauce on bottom of Pyrex dish.
Add boneless chicken breast.
Pour dressing over chicken and place pineapple on top.
Spread green pepper on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with rice.
Serves 2.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add regular sweet milk if needed to finish filling freezer.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, at medium speed of an electric mixer, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into oa greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: lamb skewers with curry sauce
directions: Place lamb and parsley in a medium size bowl.
Put egg, broth, bread, onion, salt and pepper into blender.
Cover and blend about 1 minute.
Add to meat and mix well.
Form meat into balls, using a scant 1/4 cup meat for each.
Make small fold at 1 end of a bacon slice and thread on skewer.
Push skewer through meatball. Fold bacon around it and push skewer through bacon just far enough; add next meatball and repeat.

title: the galley's honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
This recipe was given to me by Marie Helmke when she had the Galley Restaurant in Port Isabel.
This is the best honey-mustard dressing I've ever tried!

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Beat
egg
whites
until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add sugar.
Add
flavorings
and
fold	in
coconut
and corn flakes. Drop
by
teaspoon	onto a well greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet as soon as taken from oven.
Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple sorbet
directions: Place the sugar and water in a pan and heat on low or medium until the sugar dissolves.
Remove from the heat and allow to cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup tomato sauce.
In large bowl combine turkey, bread crumbs, Egg Beaters, onion, garlic, oregano and remaining tomato sauce.
Shape into 9 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 375° or a lesser heat (I bake at 350°) for 45 minutes or until done.
Spread reserved tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and cool.
Place onion rings and bell pepper on top.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over mixture and let stand overnight.
Great for reunions!!!!!!!

title: summer salad
directions: Heat corn oil, sugar or Sweet 'N Low, vinegar, salt and pepper and cool.
Mix green beans, lima beans, whole corn, onion, bell pepper and tomatoes together.
Mix all together and chill 24 to 48 hours.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with cold water and let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain well.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed and bring to a boil (rolling).
Pour over drained cucumber mixture and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Really good with dried beans.

title: onion hamburgers
directions: Combine meat, eggs, flour, catsup, salt and pepper.
Saute onion in butter.
Form meat into round cakes (4 to 6).
Put onions on half of cake and top it with another cake (sandwich-style). Wrap with bacon strips and fasten with toothpicks.
Broil or outdoor grill for 25 minutes.
Can make to size burgers you like; time of cooking can change.
Can also add mushrooms in middle of burgers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Use three 8-inch wax paper lined layer pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter or margarine and shortening and beat well. Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in carefully the beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: banana freeze
directions: Substitution for Buttermilk:
Mix one cup milk and 1 tablespoon of vinegar; let stand for about 20 minutes.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In glass baking dish, add enough water to cover bottom.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces and rub margarine on chicken and place in dish.
Cover dish with lid or foil and bake about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soup.
Cover, return back to oven and bake 30 minutes longer.
Take out of oven. Serve with rice and vegetables.

title: barley bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup tepid water in a large mixing bowl; let stand about 10 minutes.
Scald milk; add shortening, butter, sugar
and	salt.
Stir.
Add
1 cup room temperature water
and check for temperature between 110° and 140°.
Pour this
mixture into bowl with yeast and stir.
Add 3 cups bread flour and beat thoroughly.
Add 3 cups oat flour a little at a time
and
blend; add
oat
flour
until dough consistency is reached and knead 5 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine strawberry ice cream, cold milk and mashed banana.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: mustard grilled pork chops with salsa
directions: Combine mustard, honey and garlic powder in a small bowl.
Rub this mixture on pork chops.
Place chops on a hot grill; lower the hood on the grill and grill 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Garnish with the salsa before serving (the pork chops may also be cooked in the oven until tender).

title: zucchini carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until frothy.
Gradually beat in oil. Combine dry ingredients.
Add to batter.
Beat 4 minutes.
Stir in carrots, zucchini and nuts.
Pour into three greased 9-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool thoroughly.

title: crab soup
directions: Place celery, carrots and onion in a large saucepan containing 2 quarts hot water.
Cook until half tender.
Add corn, green pepper, pickling spices, red and white pepper, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Cook 1 hour.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in mincemeat and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water with ice cubes for 2 hours and drain.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil for a brine and add pickles.
Boil just to heat through.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Boil 4 quarts of water and bay leaves.
Add brisket and simmer 3 hours, partly covered.
Add rest and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.

title: 2-minute fudge
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together in 1 1/2-quart casserole until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to thoroughly blend in all of dry ingredients).
Put butter over top in center of dish.
Place in microwave oven and cook about 2 minutes or until feels warm on bottom of dish.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
If all butter had not melted in cooking, it will as mixture is stirred.
Blend in nuts; pour into buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish or pan.
Chill 1 hour in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 34 squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: You may use fresh or frozen corn, or half and half canned or frozen.
Beat eggs well; add all of the rest of the ingredients. Pour in casserole and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients together and shape into a roll.
You may want to garnish with lemon slices or parsley.

title: low-fat baked potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Brush each with olive oil.
Sprinkle with your favorite seasonings and herbs. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: herbed hamburgers
directions: Saute onion in cooking oil until tender, then drain oil.
Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl.
Form into 4 hamburger patties.
Grill hamburgers until done, about 5 minutes on each side, depending on grill temperature.

title: tupperware bread
directions: Place the flour into the Fix-N-Mix Tupperware bowl and make a well.
Cool the scalded milk with the cold water.
Add sugar, salt, eggs and yeast to the milk and water mixture.
Pour liquid into the well.
Put on the lid and wait until the lid pops off, about 1 hour.
Melt the oleo and mix all together.
Add more flour, if necessary, and knead to proper consistency, not too stiff.
Put lid back on and wait until the lid pops off again. Make into bread or rolls.
Let rise 20 minutes and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, remove from bones and cut in bite-size pieces. Put in 9 x 11-inch buttered casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crush crackers very fine.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Pour over the melted margarine and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
This reheats very well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and add pecans last.
Put in unbaked pie shell as you would a custard pie.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, onions, bell peppers and pimento.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in saucepan.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well.

title: chile and eggs(good for a buffet.)
directions: Place chiles and grated cheese in baking dish. Combine eggs and sour cream. Pour over chiles and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set in the middle. Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss chicken breast(serves 8)
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray.
Place breasts in pan 1-inch apart.
Top each chicken breast with one slice of cheese (2 slices are better).

title: chocolate candy
directions: Combine Pet milk and confectioners sugar.
Cook until a rolling boil, then continue to cook for 3 minutes, stirring all the time.
Take from fire and add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme and stir.
Pour into buttered dish or drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together on high speed with mixer.
Pour into 10-inch greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda and add to egg mixture alternating with fruit cocktail.
Grease pan with butter.
Pour in cake mixture and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ruby red pretzel dip
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 7 ingredients; whisk over medium heat until smooth.
Combine flour and cold water until smooth; add to cranberry mixture.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Transfer to a bowl.
Stir in food coloring, if desired.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serve with pretzels.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: chickamaugas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce to beef and mix well.
Warm tortillas in microwave 10 seconds until soft and pliable.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons sauce mixture in the middle of each tortilla; sprinkle with cheese.
Wrap tortilla into an envelope (bottom, top, then sides together) and fasten with a toothpick.
Either fry in oil, turning after browned, and drain; or bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 400° until crisp.

title: my mama's tea cakes
directions: Make stiff dough with the flour.
Roll out very thin; cut with cutters.
Bake at 350°.
Do not overcook.
Do not let brown.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt margarine; blend in sugar and eggs.
Add flour to mixture and cream well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mighty good corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix meal, eggs, oil and corn.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into a greased and preheated skillet and bake until brown, about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Turn it all into green fluff in a blender.
Garnish with paprika and use as a dip for raw or deep fried vegetables or pour over a baked potato.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide evenly into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fudgy pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add sugar, salt, eggs and corn syrup; blend thoroughly.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into unbaked shell, placing pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool; cover and let stand 8 hours before serving.
Garnish with sweetened whipped cream.

title: savory baked haddock
directions: Thaw frozen fillets; skin fillets.
Place in single layer in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from fat.
Add to bread crumbs and parsley.
Cook onion in bacon fat until tender. Spread over fish.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until fish flakes easily.
Yields 6 servings.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients, drop by spoonsful on buttered baking sheet.
Bake until light and brown.

title: curry rice salad
directions: Cook rice according
to
directions and cool.
Saute or boil shrimp.
Chop up celery and bell pepper.
Fry and crumble bacon. Stir in
bacon,
mayonnaise
and
Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with curry powder.
Can substitute curry rice with yellow rice and 1/2 teaspoon of curry powder.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white stiff; add soda, salt and brown sugar, mixing well.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by spoonful on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef, onions and carrots until roast is falling apart. Grind beef, onions, carrots, and green pepper.
In same pan, cook all ingredients in same juice from roast.
Cook until meat is dry or juice is gone.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Top with cole slaw.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Brown chicken in 4 tablespoons butter and spices.
Add onion and brown.
Add tomato sauce and 1 can water.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender.
Add 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in 1 cup of rice; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
When ready to serve, brown 4 tablespoons butter and pour over chicken and rice.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Rinse raisins and nuts in hot water.
Drain.
Add to flour, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar-free holiday nog
directions: Combine pudding mix, 2 cups milk, vanilla and sugar substitute in bowl.
Mix according to pudding directions.
Pour into a half-gallon container with a tight fitting lid.
Add 3 cups milk. Shake well.
Add evaporated milk and shake well.
Add remaining milk and shake well.
Chill.
One serving diabetic exchange:
1 skim milk and 1/4 starch.

title: southern style chicken curry
directions: Saute onions in large skillet until soft.
Stir in chicken and curry powder.
Add sugar, pinches of seasonings and chicken broth. Stir all together.
Bring to boiling point, then turn to simmer. Cook, uncovered, but stir occasionally.
The curry is done when the chicken is tender and sauce thickens.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken (water enough to cover) until tender.
Add salt, pepper, celery salt and onion salt.
Let chicken cool and debone. Cook tomatoes with chopped onions, peppers, garlic and mushrooms until tender.
Take 1/4 of chicken stock; bring to a boil and add spaghetti, cook 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Put chicken, vegetables and spaghetti in casserole; cook 30 minutes on low heat.
Add cheese just before serving.

title: never-fail peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a Dutch oven; cook over low heat until mixture spins a thread (230° to 234°).
Add peanuts; cook to soft crack stage (about 290°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, soda and salt; mix well.
Spread mixture thinly onto 2 warm, buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pans.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yield:
About 2 pounds.

title: easy mexican dish
directions: Heat corn and chili in saucepan.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix muffin mix as on package, using egg and milk.
Spread mixture as evenly as possible over chili.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: macaroni beef dish
directions: Brown onions; add beef and brown.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, parsley, oregano leaves and garlic powder.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Pour in 1-quart casserole. Mix well.
Add 1/2 cheese and stir.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry frappe
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water, about 5 minutes.
Cook cranberries in boiling water until soft, then put through strainer.
Add sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to boil and add soaked gelatin.
Cool.
Turn into freezing box and place in freezer. Delicious with chicken or turkey.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 24 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour dressing over cut up vegetables and marinate overnight. Turn or stir 3 or 4 times during marination.

title: chinese chicken stubs
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass baking dish.
Add chicken stubs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour; turn once during the hours.
Makes an excellent main course!

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soy sauce together.
Spread over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, oats, egg substitute and 1/2 cup V-8 juice.
Add onions and peppers thoroughly.
Add spices and taco seasoning. Form into loaf.
Place aluminum foil in loaf pan and place loaf in and cover well.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let cool a little bit.
Pour ketchup or juice on top.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Make sure all ingredients are mixed well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine eggs, bacon and cheese in a bowl.
Place a scant tablespoonful of the egg mixture in the center of a piece of bread.
Top each slice with one of the remaining slices of bread.
Cut and seal tarts using 3-inch cutter.
Brush lightly with butter.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly toasted.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar and eggs.
Mix baking soda into sour milk.
Add to mixture.
Put salt and baking soda in flour and sift into batter.
Add bananas and nuts. Bake at 300° or 350° for about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl in the order listed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together and let congeal.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla or pure lemon extract, nutmeg, butter and mashed sweet potatoes.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer or until the pie is set.

title: creamed salmon(old english recipe)
directions: In large saucepan, saute chopped onion in oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Add milk on low simmer.
Drain salmon liquid; add to onion and milk.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk.
Stir in onion and chicken (you can also add chopped broccoli).
Place 1/4 cup of mixture on each roll.
Fold edges of each roll around filling.
Brush tops of rolls with melted margarine.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: kota pilafi(baked chicken with rice)
directions: Cook onions in a Dutch oven with 8 cups water until partly done.
Add chicken parts, garlic, olive oil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook chicken until 2/3 done.
Spray a roasting pan with Pam.
Place chicken in pan.
Mix canned chicken broth and tomato sauce with seven cups of chicken stock, trying to get all of the onions, too.
Pour this broth mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle in the rice.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until rice is done. Stir a few times during the hour to mix rice up well with broth. Add more broth or water if necessary so rice won't be dry.
Before serving, burn 1/2 pound or more of butter and pour over chicken and rice.

title: pear cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flour and cinnamon to creamed mixture.
(Sift flour and cinnamon together 3 times first.)
Add vanilla.
Fold in pears and nuts.
Bake in tube pan in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix in baking pan pineapple, cherries and sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix over this and top with nuts.
Pat with oleo or butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easter bunny or frosty rolls
directions: Sift sugar, 3 cups flour and yeast.
Stir butter into boiling water until melted.
Add cold water.
Stir in sifted mixture and eggs.
Beat with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Knead enough of remaining flour into the dough to make it non-sticky, holding together.
Cover with a clean towel and allow to double.
Here's where the children take over:
Roll into 8-inch snake a handful of dough.
Tie into a loose knot and place on a cookie sheet.
The knot is the bunny's face.
The ends are his ears.
Decorate with raisins or nuts or red hots.
Allow to double.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Supposedly this recipe freezes, but we devour the bunnies hot with honey.

title: venison scallopini
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces, about 1/4-inch thick, and pound with a wooden mallet.
Dredge each piece in seasoned flour.

title: eggless vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine in ice cream maker.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring water, salt and coconut milk to the boil.
Add rice and continue to cook on medium heat until rice is almost soft; stir occasionally.
Add milk, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, almonds and vanilla and continue to cook on medium heat.
Stir often until liquid is absorbed and rice is cooked and soft.
Serve hot or cold in individual dishes with a teaspoon of jam or jelly on top.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add each egg yolk, separately mixing after each addition.
Add flour, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Beat egg whites with salt and fold in.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: ruby red fruit punch
directions: Cut 3 nice slices from each fruit.
Place in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix other ingredients and chill.
When ready to serve, place a few cubes of ice in punch.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: This cake does not have shortening or butter in it.

title: louisiana dirty rice
directions: To heated oil, add onions, celery and green onions.
Saute until soft, at least 10 minutes.
Add parsley, ground beef, livers and garlic; brown meat thoroughly.
Add sherry and other liquids. Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat; add rice and mix well.
Serves 4.

title: easy onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/2-inch slices, separated into rings.
Dip into milk, then flour, then milk again and bake into flour.
Deep fry at high temperature until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: calico quiche
directions: Microwave Method:
Place pie shell in Pyrex pie plate. Microwave on High 5 or 6 minutes or until bottom is dry and flaky. Place glass right side up in center of crust.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread mix per directions on package.
Let cool. Crumble mixture and place in a large bowl.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Combine both mixtures together.
Place in covered dish in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: sparkling fruit molded salad
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, soften gelatin in water.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until gelatin is dissolved (3 to 5 minutes).
In large bowl, stir together sugar and dissolved gelatin.
Stir in ginger ale, lime peel and lime juice. Refrigerate until slightly thickened (about 45 minutes).
Pour 1 cup gelatin mixture into greased 6-cup mold; refrigerate remaining slightly thickened gelatin.
Add red grapes to gelatin mold; refrigerate 15 minutes.
Arrange cantaloupe on top of red grape gelatin mixture; spoon over just enough thickened gelatin to cover cantaloupe.
Arrange green grapes on top of cantaloupe gelatin mixture.
Spoon remaining thickened gelatin over green grapes. Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate; garnish with lime slices.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and let dough rise.
Roll out and spread with butter.
Cut into different pieces (strips) and layer in bread pan.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Let rise until size doubles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Spread in an 11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish (after spraying with no-stick Mazola). Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: durbin hotel sugar cream pie
directions: Heat butter, 1 cup sugar and 2 cups milk in top of double boiler until butter melts.
Add cornstarch and milk mixture to it and continue cooking and stirring until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 400° oven for about 5 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Place in casserole dish and pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water over patties.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: rose's lace oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two cookie sheets with aluminum foil, shiny side up, and lightly butter the foil.

Gently melt the butter in a saucepan, then leave it until cool but still liquid. Mix in the oats and sugar just enough to blend; do not overmix. Lightly beat together the egg and vanilla; quickly stir them into the oatmeal batter.
The mixture will be very runny.
Drop it by the teaspoon onto the lined baking sheet, leaving at least 4 inches between cookies so they'll have room to spread.
Bake the cookies for 4 minutes, then lower the oven to 325° and bake another 4 minutes, until the sugar caramelizes and the edges turn brown.

title: chocolate peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and confectioners sugar; mix well.
Pat this mixture down into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt candy bar and smooth on top of peanut butter mixture.
Let cool before cutting.

title: potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes and place in large stock pot. Add butter and just enough water to cook potatoes without having them stick. At the same time cook and drain the sausage and dice the onion and crush the garlic. When the potatoes begin to fall apart, you may either continue to cook and allow potatoes to fall apart naturally or you can use a small hand blender and mix the potatoes (depending on preference for pieces of potato in your soup). Add Half and Half, chopped onion, and spices; allow to cook until onions are clear. Be careful not to turn heat too high during this time (med. low to med. depending on your stove top). As the onions begin to clear, add the sausage and allow to finish cooking. May want to serve with shredded cheese and oyster crackers.

title: koenigsberg meat balls
directions: Into a large bowl, add the bread crumbs and milk.
Saute the onion in the butter until the onion is golden.
Add to bowl along with beef, veal, anchovy fillets, egg, salt, monosodium glutamate and pepper.
Mix together and shape into balls about 2-inches in diameter.
Bring to boiling in a saucepan the water, 2 tablespoons chopped onion, bay leaf, clove, peppercorns and salt.
Carefully put the meat balls into the liquid.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove the balls with a slotted spoon and set aside to keep warm.
Strain the liquid and save.
Heat in the saucepan the 2 tablespoons butter and blend in the 2 tablespoons flour.
Heat until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add 2 cups of the liquid and the lemon juice, capers and white wine.
Bring rapidly to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Return the meat balls to the sauce and heat thoroughly.
Serve with buttered noodles.

title: south of the border chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove.

title: oatmeal peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter until fluffy. Gradually add sugars, beating well. Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well. Combine oats and baking soda; add to butter mixture, mixing well. Stir in chocolate morsels; drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: aunt bill's brown candy
directions: This makes more than 3 pounds of candy; you will find it much easier to manage if two make it together.
First, pour one pint of sugar into a heavy aluminum or iron skillet and place over low heat.
Begin stirring with wooden spoon and keep sugar moving so it will not scorch.

title: sarah's million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 40 minutes in well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.

title: peach spectacular
directions: In an 8 x 11-inch pan, mix melted oleo and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Stir once. Let cool.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks.
Add sugar, peaches and lemon juice.
Beat until it triples in volume and forms soft peaks.
Fold in whipped cream.
Arrange in layers with cooled crumbles and peach mixture.
Freeze.
Serves 12.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and extract.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Spread pie filling on top.
Sprinkle with streusel topping.

title: lo-cal fruit delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: doo doo drops
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Stir until melted on low heat.
Add cocoa, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add oats; mix well.
Spoon into cupcake tins.
Let stand until hardened.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.
One is never enough!

title: turnip green casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except crumbs and cheese. Spoon into casserole dish.
Cover top with crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This dish multiplies well for a large crowd.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Drain.
Add margarine, milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Add half of cheese; stir until cheese is melted. Pour into a casserole dish and sprinkle rest of cheese on top. Bake at 400° until cheese is melted and light brown.

title: teasers
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Cut slices into 4 triangles.
Toast on both sides.
Mix onions, bacon, mayonnaise and pepper together. Spread on toasts (use about 1 teaspoon on each triangle).
Makes 5 dozen.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lemon juice and apples.
Cook until bubbly, but do not boil.
Add lemon juice.
Keep mixture hot.
Pour over apples in jars.
Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.

title: beef and bean enchiladas
directions: In frypan, saute ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain well.
Stir in beans and taco seasoning; mix well with meat mixture.
Add taco sauce; heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Heat enchilada sauce in microwave or saucepan on low heat. Heat tortillas according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of enchilada sauce into oblong glass baking dish.
Place 1/3 cup ground beef mixture into warmed tortilla; roll and place, seam side down, in sauce-filled baking dish.
Place filled tortillas, side by side, until dish is filled.
Pour remaining sauce evenly over tortillas.
Cover with cheese.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Rinse and drain raw rice.
Add milk, sugar, margarine and eggs to the rice and mix well.
Put it into the casserole and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Stir every half hour so it won't stick.
May add raisins and cinnamon to taste. Put a small pan of water into oven while baking.

title: chip dip
directions: Melt cheese; add chili sauce and pepper.
Serve with chips (taco or potato chips).

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions for 3 minutes; drain.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, brown ground beef with onion and garlic; drain off excess fat.
Stir in sauce and simmer 10 minutes or until heated through.
Remove 1 cup meat sauce; set aside.
Stir cooked noodles into remaining sauce.
Place 1/2 noodle mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Combine Ricotta cheese with parsley; evenly spread on top of noodle mixture in casserole.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Place remaining noodle mixture on top of cheese.
Cover with reserved meat sauce and remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Mix all together very well.
Put in a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheesy chops 'n potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon cheese into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish; place in oven just until cheese is melted (5 minutes). Meanwhile, brown pork chops on both sides; drain.
Sprinkle chops with seasoned salt; set aside.
Using fork, stir milk into melted cheese until well blended.
Stir in Tater Tots and 1/2 can onions into cheese mixture.
Spread vegetables over potato mixture. Arrange pork chops over top and bake, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes or until chops are done.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more or until onions are golden brown. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: basic chicken stock
directions: Place the chicken in a large stock pot.
Add the water and bring to a boil, uncovered, over high heat, skimming off any scum. Adjust the heat so that the water bubbles gently, then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, about 3 hours, occasionally skim off the scum.

title: red potato casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over potatoes.
Drizzle oil over all.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir once.

title: layered vegetable bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 1 1/2-quart round casserole or baking dish with no-stick cooking spray.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs, parsley and butter; set aside.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in dish.
Put cheese over pineapple.
Mix juice, flour, sugar and butter; pour over cheese and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Combine first five ingredients together in a large bowl. Blend together thoroughly the remaining ingredients, then pour over mixture in bowl, stirring to coat evenly.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until cereal is hot and crisp, stirring twice.
Yield: 2 1/4 quarts.

title: mint surprise cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Chill 2 hours.
Wrap chocolate mint wafers with dough.
Top with 1/2 walnut.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions and flour.
Cut up onions and tie in a cloth bag; put in catsup while boiling.
You may adjust the amounts of spices to suit your taste.
Cook for 2 hours.
Make a batter out of 4 Tbsp. flour and add to catsup to thicken.
Stir constantly so it doesn't get lumpy.
If it does get lumpy, run through a sieve.

title: italian beef
directions: Put in a deep pan and bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve on sandwich buns.

title: easy tostadas
directions: Brown and well-drain hamburger.
Add chili beef soup and 1/2 cup water.
Heat to simmer.
When hot, layer on individual plates in this order:
corn chips, meat mixture, cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Add to taste (is optional):
chopped onions, sliced black olives and/or taco sauce.

title: black walnut cream pie
directions: Mix everything except walnuts in a double boiler.
Place over medium heat and cook until thick.
(Add cornstarch, if needed to thicken.)
Add walnuts.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Add meringue and brown.

title: cajun rice and beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray medium-size casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer in casserole, rice, beans, onion, celery and cheese.
Season each layer with small amount of seasonings and hot sauce.
Pour chicken broth over casserole.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven baked fried chicken
directions: Melt oil and butter in shallow pan at 375°.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic powder in bag.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Place chicken in oil mixture.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.
Turn and bake 10 minutes longer until crunchy.

title: crispy crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Set aside.
Beat egg and milk in bowl.
In another bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Roll chicken first in egg mixture, then in potato flake mixture.

title: breakaway bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water along with sugar.
In large bowl, pour boiling water over shortening.
Let melt, then when cool, add salt, egg, flour and yeast water.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and dip in melted oleo.
Place in oiled Bundt pan.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken; remove bones and dice into small pieces.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel, milk and onion in small dish.
Crumble Doritos. Put 4 to 6 tablespoons chicken broth in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or cake pan.
Layer chips and chicken.
Pour 1/2 sauce mixture over this.
Repeat.
Cover with grated cheese before baking.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler; stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cook, uncovered, 15 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg yolks; gradually stir in hot mixture. Return to double boiler; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Line bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with Nilla vanilla wafers; top with a layer of sliced bananas.
Pour a portion of custard over the bananas. Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard, ending with custard on top.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until mixture forms stiff peaks. Pile on top of pudding in casserole dish.
Bake in preheated oven (425°) for 5 minutes or until delicately browned.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put the 3 packages of Jell-O into a large bowl and mix well with slotted spoon.
Add the boiling water and stir well to dissolve.
Add the cranberry sauce and stir to dissolve.
Add the drained crushed pineapple, nuts and apple.
Fill green Tupperware mold halfway with mixture.
Put in freezer just until it sets so it doesn't move.

title: cheese cracker nibbles
directions: Combine flour and red pepper in bowl.
Add cheese, mixing well. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix with hands until dough is smooth.
Shape into a ball.
Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/3-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Blend margarine, flour and sugar.
Pat in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
In a separate bowl beat Dream Whip with milk and vanilla.
Blend with cream cheese mixture.
Spread on cool crust and top with cherry pie filling.

title: overnight ranch rolls
directions: Put sugar, salad oil and salt in large bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add 5 cups flour and stir well.
Add 3 eggs and yeast (does not need to be dissolved).
Add 5 or more cups of flour until dough kneads into soft ball.
Cover with bowl with lid.
Let raise until 6:00 p.m.

title: easy chicken and broccoli
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine over medium-high heat until bubbly and hot. Add chicken and cook, turning when necessary, until lightly browned on all sides, 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: florence's italian cookies
directions: Melt together the Crisco, butter and flavoring.
Mix the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add the eggs, honey, oil and milk.
Add the melted Crisco, butter and anise; mix well.
Shape cookie into balls the size of walnuts (handle as little as possible).
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Make a thin white frosting and dip the cookies while still warm.

title: tuna-taco dish(a great way for seafood)
directions: Combine tuna, cheese, olives and onion in a medium bowl. Combine sour cream, garlic powder and chili powder in a small bowl.
Add sour cream mixture to tuna mixture and toss.
Place lettuce leaves on individual salad plates.
Spoon tuna mixture on lettuce; arrange avocado and tomato wedges around tuna.
Sprinkle with
paprika.
Serve salad with tortilla chips.
Yields 4 servings.

title: date balls
directions: Simmer egg, sugar, oleo and dates until thickened.
Add Rice Krispies.
Drop by tablespoon onto a pan of coconut.
Roll and shape into balls.
Let cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs well beaten.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in alternately with the apples and vanilla.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost lightly or serve hot or cold with Cool Whip.

title: veggie soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain any liquid.
Add 1 cup flour and 2 quarts water.
Add rest of ingredients in order.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until vegetables are done then cover and cook on very low heat, 2 to 3 hours.

title: marshmallow dessert
directions: Put milk, cherry juice and marshmallows in a double boiler. Cook until the marshmallows are melted. Stir well.

Crush 10 graham crackers up and put in the bottom of a square Tupperware dish. Spoon the marshmallow mixture over the cracker crumbs. Cut the cherries into quarters and put on the top of the marshmallows. Put the chopped nuts on the top of this.
Put the Cool Whip on the top. Sprinkle the other 10 crushed graham crackers on the top of this.
Chill, cut and serve.
Very good.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add to beaten egg, oil, milk and vanilla.
Add in blueberries.
Put in muffin tins and bake at 400° until of desired doneness.
Using muffin tin liners makes clean up easier.

title: homemade pimento and cheese
directions: Cook cheese and milk until cheese is melted.
Stir constantly on medium heat.
Add egg, sugar, vinegar and pimento.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Remove from stove.
Put lid on it.
Cool completely.
Add mayonnaise and beat with mixer about 3 to 4 minutes.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in
a slow cooker pot.
Stir together well.
Cover
and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: fluffy hot cakes
directions: Combine egg, milk and cooking oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Beat smooth.
Bake on ungreased griddle.
Use Pam.
Makes 12 small cakes.
Mix just until smooth and no longer.

title: red bean toss
directions: In a bowl combine kidney beans, chili beans, celery, pickles, onion and cheese.
In a smaller bowl blend salt and Worcestershire sauce with mayonnaise.
Toss with bean mixture.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with corn chips.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy smooth.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut into small squares when cool.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and soda and add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add lemon extract and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done. Allow to stand in pan a few minutes before turning out.

title: mushroom topped pork chops
directions: Brown chops
on both sides and place in ovenproof dish. Saute mushrooms
in
butter
until
no longer moist. Mix mushrooms, parsley,
red
onions,
egg,
salt	and
pepper. Place filling on top
of
chops.
Bake
at 350° for 40 minutes. Add cheese the last 10 minutes of baking time. When tested, juice should run clear.
Serve
with salad of sliced herb tomatoes, rice or boiled new potatoes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: whiting champagne punch
directions: Chill all before mixing.
Float rainbow sherbet chunks on top. Serves a large group!

title: pumpkin or squash bread
directions: Cream
sugar and
salad oil.
Add beaten eggs, squash or pumpkin and water.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Add nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour pans.
If using disposable pans, put them on a baking sheet in the oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: instant cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl; roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Crisscross with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on crust.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian chicken wings
directions: Rinse wings and pat dry.
Place side by side in roasting pan, one layer.
Sprinkle with mixture of salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix lemon juice, sugar, soy sauce, honey, peppercorns and hot water. Pour over wings.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove cover and bake 1/2 hour.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Heat the oil in a large iron skillet and cook the shrimp just until they turn pink and begin to curl.
Remove from pan; set aside.
Reduce heat to medium and add the onions, garlic and peppers.
Cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
Add the rice and stir well to coat.
Cook for 2 minutes but do not brown.
Add the tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and stock; stir to blend.
Cover and cook over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes, or until all of the liquid is absorbed and the rice is al dente (or fluffy).
Stir in the shrimp and cook 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Beat egg yolks and sweet milk.
Put in boiler and add butter.
Cook until thick; add vanilla.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into a 10-inch unbaked pie shell or two 8-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm.
This is a very rich pie, but so delicious!

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish in oven. Cut chicken breasts in 1/2 (8 pieces).
Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs.
Lay chicken in margarine, then over.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mrs. denny's pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and cold water.
Add strawberries.
Pour over crust.
Chill until jello is firm. Sprinkle crushed pretzels on top.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add onion that has been chopped and sauteed. Add 1 can undiluted tomato soup, mushrooms, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Can add 1 small can drained yellow corn.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool. Mix the crushed pineapple and sugar together and cook for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread over cake.
Beat the pudding mix with the milk; spread over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash zucchini and cut into chunks; peel and cut onions in thin slices.
Cover vegetables with water and add salt.
Let stand two hours then drain thoroughly.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil and pour over vegetables; let stand two hours; then boil for five minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Place in canner and boil for ten minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Take the herbs from the Stove Top stuffing and the 1/4 cup butter and melt.
Place chicken in 9 x 12-inch baking dish/pan, and pour melted butter and herbs over chicken.
Place Swiss cheese over chicken and herbs until completely covered.

title: perfect spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and ginger.
Add buttermilk, margarine or butter, shortening and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on low to medium speed until well mixed. Beat 2 minutes more on high speed.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more.

title: cheesy noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Wash with hot water and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion. (Drain.)
Mix meat and all remaining ingredients together, except grated cheese.
Pour over noodles and mix lightly until noodles are coated.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: cheesecake
directions: Use ready made graham cracker pie shells (2).
Mix eggs, cream cheese, sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract (mixture may look lumpy).
Blend in sour cream.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Chill.

title: english pea salad
directions: Cook English peas as directed and drain.
Place in dish and chill.
Put a layer of chopped celery, layer of chopped onion and layer of shredded lettuce.
Cover top layer with Miracle Whip; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and Bac*Os before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain juice from beans.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix melted margarine and grated cheese with other ingredients. Roll into small balls.
Flatten with a fork on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: quiche
directions: Prick the pie shells and cook for 6 minutes at 400°.
Saute the green onions in 4 tablespoons butter until soft.
Sprinkle onions and bacon bits in equal portions over the bottom of pie shell. Top pies with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden and puffy. Serves 8.

title: yummy chocolate balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in a blender or food processor.
Set aside.
Melt chocolate bars in double boiler or microwave oven. Cool.
Fold in whipped topping and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls in cookie crumbs and roll.
Arrange on lined cookie sheet and refrigerate.
Makes 48 (1-inch) balls.

title: chicken spinach noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken
in salted water until tender, then remove the chicken and
reserve the broth.
Bone and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Saute
vegetables
in
the margarine.
Cook noodles in the reserved chicken broth, according to directions on the package,
then drain.
Mix together.
If mixture is too thick, add
broth.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter, add to sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add well beaten eggs.
Then add Karo, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans last.
(Can use halves, but chopped makes it easier to cut.)
I use food processor to fluff eggs.	Bake at 350° until middle does not shake, about 45 minutes.
Secret is not to cook too long. Also freezes well.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Combine ingredients; blend and beat until smooth.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Best served with store-bought cream cheese icing.

title: relish
directions: Grind vegetables with coarse blade.
Cover with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain, rinse and drain again.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Fill hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add cottage cheese and spaghetti sauce. Boil water and put in noodles.

title: fish chowder
directions: Melt butter; saute onion until tender.
Add tomatoes and fish. Cook until done.
In a large saucepan mix soups, milk and spices. Bring almost to a boil.
Add tomato and fish mixture.
Simmer until ready to serve.
Do not boil or milk will curdle.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend the cream cheese, chili sauce, parsley, onion and pepper sauce.
Gradually stir in tuna; beat until blended.
Pack into a 4-cup mold or small bowl.
Chill thoroughly (3 hours).
Unmold onto serving plate; serve with crackers.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients in roasting pan and marinate in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Cook, covered, in oven at 275° for 12 hours.
Remove from oven and shred with fork.
Add 1 cup catsup and 3/4 cup brown sugar to barbecue and cook for 15 minutes longer. Serve on hot onion rolls.
This makes approximately 30 sandwiches. The meat can be frozen in small portions, thawed, heated and served in minutes.

title: cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Dissolve 1 tablespoon cinnamon candies in boiling water. Arrange apple slices in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cinnamon flavored water over top. Combine cake mix, brown sugar and melted butter in a large bowl. Stir until thoroughly blended (mixture will be crumbly).
Sprinkle crumbs over apple slices. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve with whipped topping, crushed cinnamon candies and mint leaves, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil the chicken breasts until done.
Cool and take meat from bones and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain the mixed vegetables.
Measure out 2 cups strained chicken broth.
Add the soup to the broth and mix.
Add the vegetables and mix.
Pour over chicken.
Mix the melted butter, flour and milk.
Pour this mixture over the chicken and vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: crab and corn cream soup
directions: Microwave.
In a 3 quart glass casserole melt butter on High 1 minute.
Add
chopped
onion,
celery,
thyme
and
red pepper. Cover.
Cook on
High 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk, corn and surimi.
Cover;
cook
on High 7 minutes until boils. Serve with toast rounds.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot dog stew
directions: Brown onions and peppers in butter; add all other ingredients and simmer until potatoes are done.
Serves 4.

title: orange glazed cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are moistened.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Crush crackers finely with hand or rolling pin.
Line baking dish.
Lay out one layer of oysters; salt and pepper, then dot with butter.
Layer cracker crumbs, repeating with oysters, salt, pepper and butter ending with cracker crumbs and butter on top.
Saturate with oyster liquid and milk.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 40 minutes. Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, stir the sweet potatoes until thoroughly heated. Remove from heat and cream well. In a bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients and add the mixture to the potatoes. Pour the mixture into a pie plate or pan.

title: cheddar spinach quiche
directions: Drain spinach well.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add spinach, milk, eggs, bacon and seasonings.
Mix well; pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken wings
directions: If your market does not sell drummettes, buy a package of 12 chicken wings; remove wing tips and break into 2 pieces.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Put wings into shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over wings.
Bake an hour and serve warm.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in skillet and brown until meat shows no pink.
Mix rest of ingredients (I usually crumble up the bacon and put in there too).
Grease large iron skillet.
(I usually spray Pam on it before greasing it; it makes it much easier to clean and keeps the cornbread from sticking.)
Sprinkle with cornmeal and brown.
Pour half of batter into skillet; put in meat mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Pour in remaining batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mostaccioli salad(make 2 days ahead)
directions: Cook the mostaccioli as directed. Drain, then coat with the salad oil. Stir and drain again. Mix together the vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, garlic powder, mustard and parsley flakes. Pour over noodles and add the pimentos, onion and cucumber. Mix again. Lift with a fork 3 and 4 times during refrigeration and just before serving.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake(ca 1930's)
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° until done.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil in pan:
soups, chicken broth, tomatoes and onion.
In baking dish, break up Doritos.
Put chicken over chips; pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer as listed and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.
Toss and eat.

title: diabetic prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 3/4 x 5 3/4-inch loaf pan which has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauteed round steak
directions: Cut steak 1/3-inch thick into 2 x 4-inch pieces.
Dip meat pieces in flour and saute until brown.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook until meat is tender.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot butter cook mushrooms and green pepper 5 minutes.
Stir in flour until blended.
Gradually stir in half and half and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken and pimentos.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.

title: mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a large pie plate.
Prepare mashed potatoes as directed on box except decrease water to 1 cup and omit the milk.
Stir in egg and green onion.
Spread mixture evenly against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until light brown.
Cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain. Stir remaining ingredients except cheese. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spoon into shell.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 3 minutes until cheese is melted.
Garnish with sour cream, fried green pepper and tomato, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate bourbon balls
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, stirring until blended. Combine crumbs, powdered sugar and pecans in a large bowl.
Add chocolate mixture, stirring well.
Cover; let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Store in a tight container in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Blend shortening, brown sugar, peanut butter, salt and egg. Add mixed dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill overnight. Shape into 1-inch balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on baking sheet 2 to 3 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: french onion au gratin soup
directions: Slice very tender white onions and saute in butter until limp but not brown; stir constantly.
Add flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add bouillon and broth; bring to rapid boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Mix for 5 minutes at high speed.
Mix sugar, Crisco, egg whites, vanilla, salt and food coloring.
For roses and other flowers, keep cool.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add 1 cup milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring briskly until thickened. Remove from heat.
Beat egg with remaining 1 cup milk.
Gradually stir into hot mixture.
Put back on heat; boil until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; add chocolate bits, butter and vanilla.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Layer as listed, except mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise; then spread on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: stir-fry
directions: Melt margarine.
Add soy sauce and garlic powder.
Brown meat. Add fresh mushrooms and brown.
Add broccoli, carrots and onion. Stir and simmer.

title: broccoli-rice
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee with herb dumplings
directions: Blend 1 cup Bisquick, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces.
Cook chicken in shortening and butter in skillet until brown.
Remove chicken; drain fat.
Mix soup and 1 1/2 cups milk in skillet.
Add chicken pieces; cover and heat to boiling.
Cook over low heat for about 45 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Stir 2 cups Bisquick, 2/3 cup milk, the parsley flakes and poultry seasoning into a soft dough.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot soup mixture.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 10 minutes. Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Add Ranch Style beans, Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushroom soup and taco sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Line bottom of pan with Doritos.
Add meat mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix egg, milk and oil.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and pour in egg mixture all at once.
Stir lightly and quickly just to mix.
Batter will be lumpy.
Grease muffin pans to about 2/3 full.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes until lightly brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cranberry-orange relish(diabetic)
directions: Wash and sort cranberries; remove orange seeds.
Grind cranberries and orange with peel through food grinder (using finest blade).
Stir in sweetener.
Chill before serving.

title: no cook mints
directions: In a bowl, mix corn syrup, butter and peppermint.
Beat well. Gradually add 2 cups of powdered sugar.
Beat.
Stir in as much of the remaining powdered sugar as possible with a spoon.

title: italian minestrone soup
directions: Cook beans in water together in large kettle 3 to 4 hours. In a large skillet, cook in olive oil the onion, garlic, carrots, celery, cabbage and potatoes.
Cover and simmer, stirring often, for 30 minutes.
Add to beans.
Also add macaroni, salt, pepper and cooked tomatoes.
Simmer together 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: glorious macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Saute pimento, onion and mushrooms in 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Add together all ingredients except crackers and place in greased casserole dish.
Cover with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and set in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in 1 stick margarine. Prepare rice according to directions on package.
Mix all ingredients, reserving half of the cheese for topping.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Serves 25.

title: corn muffin topped casserole
directions: Brown beef and cook onion; drain fat.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
Prepare corn muffin mix as directed on package; spoon into ground beef mixture.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bacon wands(microwave)
directions: Wrap each bread stick with bacon slice in a spiral.
Place 6 at a time on a paper towel on a bacon rack (for the microwave).
Cover with a paper towel.
Microwave 6 minutes on High or until bacon is crisp, turning once.
You may roll wrapped bread sticks in Parmesan before cooking.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream first 6 ingredients.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar until coated.
Do not press.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: peanut delight
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk together.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Spoon onto waxed paper and let harden.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Roll dates, nuts and candy in 1/2 cup of flour.
Sift soda and remaining flour into bowl alternately with milk.
Beat after each addition.
Stir in coconut, nuts, fruit and candy.
Bake in a large greased tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add topping. Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: aunt pearl's white fruit cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and liquid alternately.
Dust the fruit, which has been chopped if necessary, with a little extra flour.
Fold carefully into batter; fold in nuts.
Pour into a prepared tube pan.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for 4 hours.
This makes a huge cake that will fill the 10-inch tube pan to the top.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to rolling boil. Let boil for 1 minute, then add remaining ingredients and mix. Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: venison sauerbraten
directions: Wipe meat with cloth.
Place in a small earthenware crock; add vinegar and enough water to cover; add bay leaves, peppercorns, whole cloves and parsley.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Leave 3 or 4 days, turning the meat daily.
Drain off liquid, reserving it for the sauce.
Rub meat on all sides with seasoned flour. Brown it thoroughly in butter.
Add onions, carrots and 2 cups of the spiced liquid.
Cover and simmer gently about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to a hot platter.
Add gingersnaps, rolled into fine crumbs, and sugar to the gravy; cook for about 10 minutes.
Add salt, if desired.
Pour sauce over meat.
Great with potato dumplings.

title: dutch apple cake(peach or plum)
directions: Sift
together first 4 ingredients. Add next 3 ingredients. Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: riso arancia
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter over moderate heat.
Add carrots and onions.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 7 minutes or until onion is soft, but not browned.
Stir in orange rind, green beans, almonds, pistachios, honey, turmeric and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make
Roux
from
flour
and shortening.
Add flour and shortening in iron skillet and cook on medium heat until brick brown (stirring occasionally).

title: meat loaf dinner
directions: Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Spread ketchup over top.

title: ritz cracker spread
directions: Mix together.
Chill.
Great as a topping for Jell-O, too.

title: sweet buns(good bun for a picnic lunch with bologna or ham.)
directions: Let rise about 2 hrs.
Form into buns.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put water, sugar and cornstarch in heavy saucepan and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello and berries.
Chill until it starts to set, then put in a baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: judy's balsamic dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil, and blend well.
Slowly drizzle in oil while mixing.
Adjust seasonings as needed; serve over salad greens.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat Jell-O and pineapple to dissolve; don't boil.
Let cool. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip; stir until well mixed.
Chill until set.

title: pie crusts
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, water and shortening together.
Roll out thin.
This makes two pie crusts.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350°.
Test with a toothpick.
This is a very moist cake.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix well and bake 30 minutes.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk in a large bowl. Refrigerate for one hour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Do not attempt to mold this salad.

title: confetti sweet and sour slaw
directions: In large glass or stainless bowl, combine finely shredded cabbage, carrots and peppers (matchstick pieces).
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir to combine.
Cover and refrigerate until flavors blend, 30 minutes or overnight.
Stir salad just before serving.

title: almond cheddar appetizers
directions: Combine all of the ingredients. Cut bread into 1/2-inch slices and spread with cheese mixture. Cut slices in half. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° about 8 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: m&m drop cookies
directions: Mix as you would a cake.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: chili con queso bake
directions: Spread cheese in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover with green chili strips.
Beat together one dozen eggs.
Pour on top of cheese and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Cream 2 tablespoons butter
with
cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch;
add 1
egg,
2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix above ingredients (except dough). Spoon chicken mixture into center of crescent roll that has been pressed into the shape of a square (or use fillo dough).
Bring 4 corners of dough square to the center to form a square.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 4 large squares or 8 small balls.

title: black midnight devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until creamy.
Beat the eggs and add to shortening/sugar.
Combine flour, salt, soda and baking powder and sift together.
Combine cocoa and hot coffee, blending until smooth.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients, mixing until well mixed, adding vanilla last. Bake in a greased and floured 8-inch square pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: pumpkin squares(this is a scrumptious recipe.)
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in an ungreased baking sheet (15 x 10 x 1-inch) and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cooled, spread on Pumpkin Square Topping.

title: pear honey
directions: Slice pears and put through a food chopper.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and sugar.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and place in a hot water bath, boiling, for 10 minutes. Makes 4 pints.

title: peaches (vinegar) dried
directions: Mix and cook over low heat.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Cook until peaches are soft and liquid has decreased enough to use peaches to make half-moon pies.
Freeze or put into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Note: just the peelings can be used this way and they are good too.

title: radio pudding
directions: Bring 3 cups milk and sugar to a boil.
Mix together the egg yolks, salt, cornstarch and 1 cup milk; add to hot mixture, cooking and stirring until thick.
Cool.
Add the vanilla.
Put into large casserole.

title: never fail chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour, then add milk and water. Cook in double boiler until very thick. Take off heat to cool; beat in egg yolks. Place in raw pie crust. Bake until done.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine water, bouillon cubes, carrot, celery, onion and potatoes and cook.
Cook frozen vegetables separately.
When done add cream of chicken soup.
Add cheese last.
Cook and stir until cheese is all melted.

title: birthday party punch
directions: Use a tablespoon of brown sugar to sweeten 1 cup of whipping cream.

title: summertime punch
directions: Pour liquids into bowl.
Slice orange, lemon and lime into 1/2 moons.
Add lime and orange sherbet just before serving.
Float sherbet balls in bowl.

title: banana bread
