directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Separately mix together egg, oil and bananas.
Stir this into the dry ingredients.*
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Check after 7 minutes, should be brown around edges.
Lift with spatula carefully.
Will become crisp when cool.

title: tater tot hamburger casserole
directions: Mix hamburger with chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste. Line bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan with raw mixture; do not pack. Cover hamburger with Tater Tots.
Mix soup and milk; pour over all.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: mom's autumn-crunch pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift and measure flour and sugar into mixing bowl which will hold entire amount.
In medium saucepan, combine oil, buttermilk, cocoa and Coca-Cola; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Mixture will be thin and marshmallows will float to top.)
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan at 350°.
(Insert toothpick in center of cake, if it comes out clean, cake is done.)

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously butter a 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with soda crackers (about 40).
Melt butter; add brown sugar and vanilla.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes (time for accuracy).
Pour over soda crackers; spread evenly.
Bake 5 minutes.
Place on cooling rack.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Wait 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate evenly over top.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into bars (about 80).
Wait 20 minutes and remove from pan.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Put American cheese (cut up) into soup mixture and warm to melt cheese.
Add ham to mixture and blend well.
Place macaroni into a buttered casserole dish and pour soup mixture over it.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook flour, butter and milk until smooth.
Add cheese to sauce and stir until melted.
Mix broccoli and onion with cheese sauce.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Add bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strips
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
When dough is well mixed, cover for an hour with bowl, then roll out until thin and cut into strips, one inch wide and 4 inches long.
Cook in deep grease; use Crisco oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and pie filling.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together the flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, cream together the Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; blend after each addition.
Add flour mixture.
Add milk last.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: italian pie
directions: Partially thaw spinach, squeezing out excess liquid.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and spinach.
In bowl stir together beaten eggs, Mozzarella, Ricotta, Parmesan cheese and marjoram.
Sprinkle flour on 1 pie crust.
Line pie plate with flour side down.
Spoon Ricotta mixture into crust.
Top with beef mixture.
Top with remaining crust; seal and flute.
Cut slits in top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 30 minute cheesecake
directions: Cream together and pour over crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° to 375° or until done in center.

title: scalloped potatoes(microwave)
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and water in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover; microwave 8 to 9 minutes on High or until potatoes are just about tender.
Set aside.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats in yogurt for 30 minutes.
In mixing bowl combine margarine, Fruit Sweet and applesauce.
Mix well.
Blend in slightly beaten egg whites.
Add oat mixture and beat well.
In separate bowl combine dry ingredients, then add to batter until well blended.
Pour into 12 muffin cups which have been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Heat brown sugar and margarine on stove until bubbly.
Remove, add milk and stir well.

title: macaroni and dried beef casserole
directions: Seal with foil and put in refrigerator for one day. Remove foil and bake for 1 hour at 375° in 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: dip for apples
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Mix with milk and vinegar.
Keep warm in fondue pot and serve with sliced apples.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Hard boil eggs and while they cook, mix soups together.
Place asparagus in a casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over asparagus. Sprinkle pepper over top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
As casserole bakes, peel and slice eggs.
Remove casserole from oven; arrange sliced eggs on top and serve.

title: pickled asparagus
directions: Combine boiling water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar and chill.
Wash and clean asparagus. Break stalks into 1 1/2 inch chunks or leave whole.
Blanch in boiling water.
Return to boiling; boil 2 minutes for chunks or 3 minutes for whole stalks.
Immerse in ice water until cool.
Pack pint jars with asparagus.
Add garlic and dill to 1 inch from top with chilled mixture.
Boil in water bath 15 minutes after water returns to a boil.
Note:
21 lbs. of fresh asparagus makes 15 pints long spears and 6 pints cut up chunks.
Takes 16 recipes of syrup.

title: savory turkey loaf
directions: Beat together egg, applesauce, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning in mixing bowl.
Add turkey, wheat germ and onion.
Mix lightly.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: peppermint whip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and extract. Place bowl of gelatin in large bowl of ice water; stir until slightly thickened.
Whip until about doubled in volume.
Blend in the whipped topping.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes. Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Put strips of dough on top of pie.
Bake until crust is done.

title: sherbet punch
directions: In a bowl, mix the ginger ale and lemonade (don't add water to lemonade); dissolve.
Add cherries with juice.
Float fruit rings. Add sherbet last.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Wash in cold water.
Brown meat.
In a bowl mix seasonings, 1/2 Parmesan cheese and egg. Place first layer of noodles in a flat pan.
Add meat.
Spread a thick layer of spaghetti sauce on noodles.
Spread a layer of each Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Next, layer seasoning mixture. Repeat with other layers.
On the top layer, add remaining sauce, cheese's, including remaining 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind all ingredients together.
Mix, chill and serve.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Combine pumpkin and canned milk.
Beat eggs with granulated sugar and spices.
Combine these 2 mixtures together and mix well.
Pour over crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: citrus mint cooler
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cover, remove from heat and let steep until cool.
Strain.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: no frosting diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in plain water until water is gone.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil. Mix well.
Blend in baking soda, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add vanilla.
Mix. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8 x 11-inch pan. Cake also freezes good.

title: taco salad
directions: Crush chips.
Dice tomatoes and onion.
Tear lettuce.
Brown ground beef.
Shred cheese.
Drain the liquid off the beans.
In a very large bowl layer the ingredients: chips, lettuce, beef, onion, tomatoes, beans, dressing and cheese.
Repeat until everything is used.
Best if refrigerated overnight before eating.

title: pat's potato salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl place cooled potatoes and cooled eggs. Add remaining ingredients and add just enough pickle juice to make the consistency stirable.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, melted and cooled oleo and eggs. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put drained crushed pineapple on 1st layer.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs with mixer. Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients and form into a ball. Roll out between 2 sheets of Saran Wrap. Take top piece of Saran off. Transport to a 9 to 10-inch pie plate. Invert the Saran wrap and lower pie crust into plate, then peel Saran off.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter to make crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hanky panks
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage.
Pour off grease.
Add Velveeta cheese and seasoning.
Will be very thick.
Keep on burner.
Put on party rye.

title: crock-pot beef roast
directions: Season the roast and mix the soups.
Pour over the beef in the crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: pink refresher
directions: Combine ice cream and cranberry juice in blender.
Cover. Blend until smooth.
Pour ice cream mixture into tall beverage glasses filling 1/2 full.
Add ginger ale to fill glasses. Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.

title: heavenly onions
directions: Slice onions and separate rings.
Saute in butter.
Simmer in heavy pan over low heat.
Stir frequently until clear.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with 1/2 pound grated Swiss cheese. Sprinkle with pepper.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add next three ingredients.
Cool melted margarine to room temperature.
Add margarine and other 2 ingredients to sugar mixture.
Stir together well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: sugar-free cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries, oranges and apples.
Add to jello made with 3 cups water.
Add pineapple and add sweetener.

title: peanut chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve as a sandwich filling, stuffed in a tomato or on lettuce.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in 3 pieces, boil tips in broth for more flavor. Discard tips.
Soak remaining wings in salted water (2 tablespoons salt) for 1 hour, then rinse in clear water.
Pat dry.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, let stand 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook and cool carrots.
Mix soup, salad oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour over carrots, onion and bell pepper.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: company eggs
directions: Layer greased 9-inch pie plate with hash browns brushed with butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Sprinkle with ham, grated cheeses, rather lightly beaten eggs and milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Make lime jello according to package instructions.
Let jell in clear dish.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup water.
Add marshmallows.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple juice and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended and cool slightly.
Fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Chill and pour over layer of jelled lime jello.

title: sweet and sour barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Simmer over low heat for 1 hour. Use on chicken, pork chops, ribs or hamburger.
Yields 3 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients well, adding peanut butter last and beating until smooth.
Pour into unbaked shell and bake 45 minutes in slow oven.
Increase heat after 30 minutes.
Bake until firm.

title: taste good cucumbers
directions: Wash, but do not peel, cucumbers. Slice thin. Add a small amount of oil and a small amount of vinegar. Mix in sugar, salt and pepper to taste.

title: mango bread
directions: Grease and flour a 1-pound loaf pan.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, beat together the vegetable oil and sugar, blending well.
Stir in the flour mixture with the eggs.
Beat in the vanilla extract.
Stir in the mango.
Fold in the raisins and coconut.
Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan and set aside to rest for about 20 minutes or until batter bubbles slightly.
While batter rests, preheat oven at 350°.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until the top springs back when lightly pressed.
Remove and cool on rack.
Slice and serve with ice cream, fruit sherbet or as a snack.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Bake as directed on box.
When cool, split each layer so that there are 4 layers.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter for 2 minutes in large pan. Add broth and bring to boil.
Add raw noodles and boil for 12 minutes.
Add broccoli and milk and pepper.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes. Add cheese.
Cook at low temperature until noodles are done.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, mix whipped topping and cottage cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: easy apple pie(low sugar)
directions: Spread apples in pie shell.
Mix sugar and spices and sprinkle on apples.
Pour on margarine and top with second pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop your popcorn and place in a brown grocery sack (about 1/2 full).
Microwave the brown sugar, corn syrup, oleo and salt on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in soda and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Pour over popped popcorn (leave in sack).
Shake sack so that all popcorn is covered.
Place sack in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Spread out on wax paper to cool.

title: pumpkin harvest cookies
directions: Mix flour and pumpkin pie spice.
Blend margarine, brown sugar, pumpkin and eggs.
Add flour to mixture.
Add white chocolate and pecans.
Chill mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and salt.
Mix in melted butter and syrup.
Stir in 1 cup pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Dilute coffee in 1/2 cup water.
Add sugar to rest of water. Boil until clear.
Cool.
Add coffee.
Mix and add vodka and vanilla.
Put in jars or bottles.
Shake daily for three weeks. Very nice gifts.

title: heart healthy mediterranean stew
directions: Broil beef on rack about 20 minutes or until rare, turning once.
Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Add onion and beef; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove garlic, bay leaf and cinnamon stick before serving.
May be thickened with flour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken, onion and pepper until chicken is tender.
Then add salsa and rice. Cover with cheese.
Cover with lid.
Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Fry the meat; salt and pepper to taste.
Add the onions; cook until the onions are clear.
Drain the extra fat.
Add the mustard, catsup and soup.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add a little water if it becomes too dry.
Serve on buns.

title: steamed vegetables
directions: Steam in steamer or double boiler for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: moms chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Add pudding mix, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan. Chill until ready to fill.

title: oyster soup
directions: Chop white and green onions and pepper. Saut in 1/2 cup butter. When lightly browned, add parsley and thyme. Add the minced garlic last. Using 6-quart container, combine the sauted mixture, oysters and juice with enough water for the mixture to cook. Cover and gently cook the oysters and seasoning for 1 hour. When the oysters are done, scald 2 quarts of milk. Stir the milk into the oysters, 1 cup at a time.

title: jiffy spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet, stirring to crumble. Drain and return to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice, stirring to mix.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover and remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Melt butter in glass pie pan on High for 45 seconds in microwave.
Stir in crumbs and sugar.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened in pie plate.
Press up sides and bottom.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes, rotating 1/2 turn after 1 minute.
Cool.
Beat peanut butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together well.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour in crust and refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Fry chicken in margarine until well done.
Put in a large casserole dish or large Pyrex bowl.
In separate bowl, mix rice and 2 cans of soup.
Add thyme, celery flakes and parsley flakes. Pour rice mixture onto the chicken.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Break up roast beef, removing any fat.
Combine beef, soup, peas, carrots, onions, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add potato chips. Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Press with the bottom of a tumbler or heavy glass dipped in sugar.
(I use one with a fluted design.) Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add potatoes and clam nectar and boil until tender in 1 1/2 cups water.
Remove from heat.
Thoroughly mix cream cheese and flour, then add to potato mixture and mix well.
Add celery and milk and bring to a hard boil.
Then add minced clams and boil 5 minutes.

title: katy's korner quiche lorraine
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in drippings.
Cook until tender.
Combine crumbled bacon, vegetables, cheeses, eggs, sour cream, salt and pepper. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until slightly browned on top.
Serves 6.

title: carrot coconut cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside.
Beat margarine, sugar and eggs in medium bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until creamy.
Alternately stir in milk and flour mixture until blended.
Mix in carrots, coconut, walnuts and pineapple with juice until blended.
Spread into 2 greased 9 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pans;
cool completely on wire racks.
Frost cake with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting. Garnish with coconut and carrot flowers, if desired.

title: brown butter icing
directions: Heat butter or margarine over low heat until golden brown. Blend in 4 cups 10x sugar.
Add cream, oil and vanilla.
Beat to consistency to spread.
Sprinkle rest of nuts on top.

title: harmony heights frozen peaches
directions: Thaw orange juice; add sugar and heat to dissolve sugar.
Set aside.

title: california shrimp
directions: Heat soup, cream and cheese in double boiler until cheese is melted. Add shrimp and almonds. Cook until heated thoroughly. Serve over asparagus, chow mein noodles or rice.
Amount of shrimp and almonds are variable.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: dirt
directions: Blend the cream cheese and 1 cup 10x sugar.
Beat together until thick the vanilla pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Mix the 2 mixtures together.
Grind the cookies. Layer, starting with Oreo cookies, pudding, Oreos, etc., ending with Oreo cookies.
Makes one flowerpot.
Serve in a flowerpot; may decorate with silk flowers or gummy worms.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion, blending well. Add broccoli and cheese while blending.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat. Add taco seasoning and Ranch dressing. In large pot, add meat and other ingredients. Cook about 30 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients plus 1/2 cup nuts. Form into a ball and coat with remaining nuts. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: green chili cheese grits
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch ovenproof casserole dish.
In a large saucepan, combine the grits and water.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Add the butter, cheese, salt, Tabasco, eggs and chilies (with seeds and juices) to the grits.
Pour into the prepared casserole and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours before baking.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until nicely browned.
Serves 8.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Add apples and Bran.
Blend well.
Add all dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased angel food or Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fig pickles
directions: Wash figs and sprinkle baking soda over figs.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain and wash.
Add clear hot water to figs and let boil until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet pan.
Pinch them together for the crust.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes at 350°.
See package.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add beans.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add mushroom soup to mixture.
Top with French fried onions.

title: rabbit with dumplings
directions: Add cut up rabbit to a mixture of flour, salt and pepper in
a plastic or paper bag and shake.
Brown floured meat in 3 tablespoons cooking oil.
Add enough water to cover meat and cook until tender.
Add vegetables and bay leaves.
Cook until carrots are tender.

title: lemon lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Chill until this starts to gel.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with Jell-O.
Place in mold and refrigerate until set.

title: burritos
directions: Prepare meat same as "Mike's Famous Chili".
After placing shredded beef in pot, add water to cover meat.
Add onion, pepper and frozen vegetables.
Add soy sauce, chili powder and cumin. Cook until vegetables are tender, adding water as needed to cover mixture.
Add Spanish rice.
Warm flour tortillas.
Use slotted spoon to dish meat mixture onto tortilla and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Roll up tortilla, smother with salsa and eat with a fork.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with 1 can pie filling (cherry).
Chill before serving.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat well until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; stir into first mixture.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan and cut into squares while slightly warm.
Roll or toss in powdered sugar.
Makes 16 (2-inch) chewy squares.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until tender, but don't overcook.
In a skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain meat and pour into spaghetti sauce; simmer.
In a casserole dish, layer a little sauce, then noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce to cover all noodles.
Bake 45 minutes or until real bubbly.
Let set 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and margarine.
Add flour, salt and paprika to make a roux.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Gradually add the chicken broth, mix until smooth.
Then add scalded milk and mix until smooth.
Cook carrots and celery in water until tender.
Drain and add to the soup.
Add cheese.
Bring to serving temperature. Makes about ten 8-ounce servings.

title: hot bacon cheese spread
directions: Cut top from the bread, scoop out the inside, leaving a 1 inch thick shell.
Cut removed bread into bite size pieces and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spoon into bread shell. Replace top of the bread; wrap in foil.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Serve with bread pieces and/or crackers.

title: quick ribs
directions: Cut ribs as you would if putting in oven; boil until well done and tender. Drain juice from ribs. Add remaining ingredients. Cook and simmer until sauce is coated.

title: mamma's lemon meringue pie
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups water.
Mix flour, cornstarch, sugar, salt and 1/2 cup cold water.
Gradually add mixture to hot water and cook until thick and transparent.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook 5 minutes.
Add butter, lemon rind and juice.
Mix well.
Cool entirely before pouring into baked and cooled pie shell.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Mix together and set aside celery soup, mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and jalapeno pepper.
Grate Cheddar cheese and set aside.
In large casserole dish, line one layer of chips, then 1/2 ground beef, a layer of soup mixture, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Put 1 cup yellow corn meal, 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon ground cumin in a 2-quart pan over high heat.
Cook, stirring, for 3 to 4 minutes, until mixture thickens and begins to lose gloss.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil and drain broccoli and pour into casserole dish.
Mix together the mushroom soup, mayonnaise, onion, eggs and cheese. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish over broccoli and mix in.
Pour crushed crackers over mixture.
Dab with a little butter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick appetizer
directions: Wash grapes thoroughly and pat dry.
Coat with sour cream. Very good.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 9x9-inch baking pan with vegetable spray.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut and cook carrots.
Grate the cheese.
Saute onion.
Mix together lightly in a baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pistachio fluff pudding
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve topped with maraschino cherry.

title: old fashioned buckwheat cakes (yeast)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour boiling water over the corn meal.
Add the buckwheat flour and buttermilk.
Combine with the yeast mixture.
Cover and let stand in a warm place overnight, then the next morning add the soda, salt, the molasses and some milk to make the batter the consistency of cream.
Now fry and enjoy.

title: peggy's special chicken bake
directions: Pour dry rice into bottom of baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts on top of rice.
Pour spice mix from Rice-A-Roni on top of chicken breasts.
Spoon cream of celery soup on top of spices and chicken.
Add 1 can water over top of mixture.
Cover with foil. Cook at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: minnie mouse's tropical treat
directions: Place 1 pineapple ring in each of 4 dessert dishes.
Place 1 scoop of sherbet on top of each pineapple ring.
Sprinkle the coconut over the top.
Place 1 cherry on top of each portion. Serves 4 people.

title: cocktail sauce(for shrimp, crab and raw vegetables)
directions: Mix all together well; store in refrigerator for a few days before serving.
This will keep indefinitely.
Also good on sandwiches.

title: citric punch
directions: Mix
citric
acid
and boiling water and let set for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Then
mix other ingredients and add to first 2 ingredients and
freeze.
When ready for use, thaw for a few minutes, chop with food chopper and add ginger ale.

title: cheese roll
directions: Allow cheese to warm to room temperature.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Shape into balls.
Roll in chili powder.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles by package directions.
Cook beef and onions in oil until meat turns white.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Beginning with noodles, layer in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese and cook until cheese melts.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit and nuts. Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Add dry ingredients and flavors. Add fruit. Oil pan well. Sprinkle pan with flour after oiling it. Cook at 275° for approximately 3 hours or until done.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain, then mix macaroni, milk, flour, eggs, sugar and mayonnaise together.
Sprinkle black pepper.
Melt margarine.
Pour into the other ingredients.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Place chicken in large stew pot.
Cover chicken with barbecue sauce and Coke.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough to cover chicken.
Cook on stove top for 1 hour or until chicken falls off the bone.
Serve sauce over potatoes or rice.

title: "come again" chicken
directions: Melt butter and brown chicken in skillet.
Sprinkle onion and celery over chicken, then pour mixture of teriyaki and ketchup over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Baste chicken a few times as it cooks.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix
peanut
butter,
butter, sugar and boiling water.
Blend
with
rotary
beater or spoon until smooth. Stir in Bisquick.
Drop
with
teaspoon
on
lightly greased baking sheet;
flatten
with
greased
glass, or press with fork dipped in flour.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until set but not hard. Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat.
Sift dry ingredients alternately with milk and chopped oranges and raisins.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°.
Makes a large cake (4 layers).

title: tamale pie
directions: Slice tamales into chunks.
Layer in large casserole dish. In middle, put layer of Fritos and cheese.
Bake until onion is done (approximately 30 minutes).

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon, in bowl.
Fry bacon in frypan.
When brown, remove bacon and crumble.
Pour mixture into bacon grease and cook until boiling.
Add bacon and pour over salad.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Use real ripe, juicy peaches.
Put in a kettle and mash up so there is plenty of juice.
If you have to add water, add very little.
To every cup of peaches, use 3/4 cup of sugar.
Add a small bit of lemon juice.
Boil a while.

title: fudge ecstasies
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, heat half of the chocolate pieces, the unsweetened chocolate and margarine until melted, stirring occasionally.
Add eggs, flour, sugar, vanilla and baking powder. Beat until thoroughly combined.
Stir in remaining chocolate pieces.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins until tender;
drain and set aside.

title: polish cabbage soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a kettle.
Let this come to a boil, then simmer until cabbage is done and potatoes are tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Fry bacon until crisp, then add bacon to soup. In bacon grease, add flour and stir until brown.
Add to soup and simmer until soup thickens.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Combine flour and sugar; blend in egg.
Add cider vinegar and juice from pineapple.
Add to flour mixture.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool and mix in Cool Whip.
Add apples and nuts. Mix together.
Keep in fridge.

title: isabell's sausage topped egg souffle
directions: *Saute sausage in frying pan, stirring constantly until sausage loses red color; it will be crumbly.
(Do this first so it will cool before spreading on top of casserole.)

title: gail's cheese things
directions: Mix.
Roll in balls.
Mash with fork.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Can put pecans on top before baking.

title: coconut delight
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; cool.
Combine the next 3 ingredients and spread over the crust.
Combine the vanilla pudding and the milk; let this mixture thicken, then spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over this, then sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: homos with tahini
directions: Cook chick peas with liquid for 5 minutes.
In mixing bowl, mix garlic salt and salt.
Add tahini paste, ReaLemon; blend hot chick peas and liquid and mix thoroughly.
Pour into mixer and puree until smooth.
Refrigerate overnight and eat as a dip.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and pepper in fat until onions are golden.
Add beef and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in rest of ingredients and pour into greased 2 qt. casserole, cover and bake 2 hour in 350 oven.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.

title: andrea's chili
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Put in colander and drain.
Put beef back in frying pan and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer.
(I like to cook mine slowly in crock-pot.)

title: buffalo chips (cookies)
directions: You will need a very large mixing bowl. Mix all ingredients together. Make any size cookie you wish. In order to have a 2 1/2 to 3-inch diameter cookie, drop the cookie dough between the size of a ping pong ball and gold ball. (I am able to get 15 cookies per cookie sheet.) Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 minutes; 15 minutes if you make a larger cookie. I usually get about 120 cookies per recipe.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat 7-up and pour over jello. When dissolved, add remaining ingredients.

title: baked haddock
directions: Place fresh haddock in glass baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix together the mayonnaise, mustard and sugar.
Spread mixture over the haddock and sprinkle with the mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees until golden brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: herbal vegetable dressing
directions: Mince the fresh herbs, reserving a few leaves to use as garnish.
Place all ingredients in a small mixing bowl.
Beat vigorously with a wire whisk until well blended.
Garnish with fresh leaves and serve immediately.

title: "wendy's frosty"(homemade chocolate ice cream)
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk and stir to blend.
Pour into 1/2 gallon ice cream freezer and add chocolate milk until the "fill line" is reached.
Stir again and mix well.
Freeze according to ice cream freezer directions.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice apples in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan. Mix all other ingredients together.
Crumble over top of apples.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, if desired.
Drain well.
In a large bowl, prepare cornbread mixes as directed on package.
Add meat, green chiles, corn and cheese.
Mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with nonstick spray.
Pour mixture into prepared dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl to combine and make a well in the center.
Whisk butter, milk, sour cream and eggs in medium bowl and pour into well.
Whisk just until smooth;
do not over mix.
Spoon about 1/4 c. of batter into center of hot waffle iron and cook.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chickens, seasoned to taste.
Cool and remove fat. Replace flavor with bouillon cubes.
Debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Boil spaghetti in the chicken broth.
Cut and saute onions, peppers and celery in margarine.
Add tomatoes, pimento, English peas, soup, Ro-Tel, Velveeta and chili powder.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until heated through.
Makes a large quantity.
Good hot or cold.
Freezes beautifully.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Combine butter and sour cream in a bowl; mix well.
Stir in baking mix.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: cornbread broccoli casserole
directions: Mix butter, onions, salt, cottage cheese, eggs and corn muffin mix together.
Stir in broccoli.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Roll meat balls (size of walnuts) in flour and brown on all sides.
Refrigerate.

title: california dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Combine eggs, cottage cheese, cracker crumbs, chilies and half the shredded cheeses. Turn
into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Top with remaining cheeses.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: mashed potato dressing
directions: Cube and brown bread in 3 tablespoons margarine (stir often to prevent burning).
Add onion salt to taste.
Mix potatoes and bread.
Add egg and enough milk to moisten.
Stuff fowl.
Leftover dressing may be placed in baking dish and cooked in moderate oven.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake 35 to 45 minutes longer, or until set.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.
Yields two 9-inch pies.

title: sloan's squash pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by the tablespoons onto buttered or oiled pan.
Cook as pancakes.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix and cook 3 hours in oven at 200°.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas and add remaining ingredients. Add enough mayonnaise to make it creamy. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: layered jello salad
directions: To each Jell-O in separate pans, add 1 cup hot water. Dissolve, then add 1/2 cup cold water to each Jell-O; chill and cut in cubes.
Bring to boil sugar, pineapple juice and lemon Jell-O. Add 1 cup cold water.
Will be soupy.
Refrigerate.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put cracker crumbs and butter in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Whip overnight Jell-O.
Add 3 colors of Jell-O. Turn over and over and add Cool Whip.
Put in crust and chill overnight.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender.
Drain and save 1/2 cup of broth.
Cool chicken; remove from bone and remove skin.
Chop chicken.
In large saucepan, saute onion and garlic 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup broth, salt and pepper, cornstarch, chicken and chilies. Cook until thick.
Saute 12 corn tortillas until pliable.
Place chicken mixture in center of each.
Fold or roll tortillas and place, seam side down in hot oil in large skillet.
Fry until golden brown; drain on paper towel and serve hot with Sour Cream Sauce.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix well and put in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 16 people.
Freezes well.
Top with chow mein noodles, if desired.

title: caramel pie
directions: Bake 3 pie crusts.
Toast in a skillet the coconut and pecans in butter; set aside to cool.
Cream together cream cheese and condensed milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Layer coconut mixture in baked crust, then Cool Whip mixture, ending with nut mixture on top.
Drizzle caramel topping on top of each pie.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Set out of freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: au gratin potatoes and ham(slow cooker)
directions: Combine everything in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours.

title: ruth bars
directions: Mix by hand the first 3 ingredients.
Add any or all of the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for only 18 to 19 minutes.
Do not overbake! Cool and cut.
You can put powdered sugar icing on while hot.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles. Place on a cookie sheet. Blend all other ingredients. Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mixture onto each rectangle. Roll the 4 corners of the crescent dough over chicken mixture to the center. Brush with melted butter or margarine. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet treats
directions: In microwave bowl, melt almond bark and peanut butter for about 2 minutes.
Mix in marshmallows, peanuts and Rice Krispies. Spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: mexican mix casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In glass pie plate, place can of chili, then can of drained corn on top of chili.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: aunt alice's spritza
directions: Blend well.
Press from cookie press in "s" shape.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes until slightly browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions on package.
Fry Italian sausage; drain.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and add drained sausage.
Layer in baking dish the tomato sauce mixture, then noodles and cheese mixture.
Repeat, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until heated thoroughly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients and pour into greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until set and lightly browned.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine ingredients, mix and serve.
(What could be easier.) Preparation Time is 5 minutes.

title: potato balls
directions: Boil potatoes 20 minutes; drain and mash.
Add cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, butter, soup mix and pepper.
Mix well.
Add 1 or 2 teaspoons of milk, if dry.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Shred zucchini and mix with eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Stir only to moisten.
Fold in nuts and raisins or dates.
Pour into floured and greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and salt; stir, then add dry milk and half the flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Then mix in gradually remaining flour until consistency of dough.
Place in greased bowl until it doubles in bulk, about 1 hour.
Knead and turn out on a floured board.
Roll into desired shapes and sizes.
Let rise another 1 hour until double in bulk.
Heat oven to 425° (hot).
Bake 10 minutes; makes 1 dozen.
If kitchen is cold, set pan in cupboard with pan of boiling water for warmth and moisture.

title: flap jacks
directions: Beat egg whites and yolks separately.
Then beat together egg yolks, sugar, salt, milk, butter, flour and baking powder.
Add whites last.
Pour out individual flap jacks on a hot griddle. Serve with melted butter and hot maple syrup which has been boiled until thick.
Top with whipped cream.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in double boiler or over low heat. Add Rice Chex until coated, mixing gently.
Place in large Tupperware container with lid.
Shake gently with powdered sugar until coated white.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks lightly and mix in 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Cook over hot water until mixture coats a silver spoon, stirring constantly. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon rind and chill. Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Gradually add the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in slightly thickened gelatin mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet potato and pecan casserole
directions: Placed cooked, sliced sweet potatoes in a 13x9x2-inch pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
When pecan pie is done, outer edges of filling will be set while center will be slightly soft.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add remainders.
Beat and add 1 cup hot coffee.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put first four ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Place 1 whole clove in each canning jar.
Add cucumbers (whole or sliced) into hot jars.
Fill with hot syrup.
Seal jars and wait at least 1 month before serving.

title: jello supreme
directions: Boil candy in 2 1/2 cups water until melted.
Add Jell-O.
Cool until Jell-O starts to set.
Add can of drained crushed pineapple. Pour half in dish and put in freezer until sets.
Add enough cream to the cream cheese to make it spreadable.
Spread over the cool set Jell-O.
Sprinkle the chopped nuts over the cheese.
Add the rest of the Jell-O and refrigerate.

title: browned rice with chile
directions: Wash rice and lay on cloth to dry.
Melt the butter; add the rice, stirring constantly until a nice brown.
Cover well with water.
Let simmer until soft (may need to drain).
Add salt and chile powder.

title: sauerbraten(spiced beef)
directions: *Enough to cover meat.

title: beef paprika
directions: Melt shortening in a large skillet.
Add meat, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until meat is brown and onion is tender. Stir in ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika, mustard, cayenne and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Cover; simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Blend flour and 1/4 cup of water.
Stir gradually into meat mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato pepperoni pizza
directions: Fry potato slices in butter with onion until potatoes are tender.
Spread tomato sauce over potatoes in pan.
Top sauce with sliced pepperoni.
Cover pepperoni with cheese.
Cover pan and heat until cheese is melted.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In a 2 1/2-quart shallow (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking dish, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions, cheese and soup.
Dot the top with margarine.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter bar
directions: Mix corn syrup, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Mix Rice Krispies and Corn Flakes together with corn syrup mixture.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Combine 1/4 cup butter, pudding mix, milk and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of cereal mixture.
Melt chocolate and remaining butter.
Spread over filling.
Cut into squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in pieces and fry.
Mix other ingredients.
Add bacon and grease.
Bake, uncovered, 3 hours at 300°.
Serves 25.

title: texas beef and black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Brown ground round and garlic in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring until meat crumbles.
Drain and place in a large bowl.
Add black-eyed peas and remaining ingredients; stir well. Place mixture in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spicy pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 3 large loaf pans or 7 mini-loaf pans and dust with flour.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and cloves.
Set aside.

title: diet soup
directions: In a large pan, mix together all ingredients.
Cook until hot.

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Break bread into small chunks and place in a large bowl.
Add milk and sherry; stir well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar, raisins, 2 tablespoons butter and vanilla; add to bread mixture, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine honey and remaining 2 tablespoons butter; pour over bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Serve warm with Whiskey Sauce.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Take flour, shortening and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Take out 1 cup crumbs and keep for top; to the rest of the crumbs add boiling water, molasses and soda.
Mix well, then pour into a greased 9 x 9 or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and bake at 350°
until done.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a 12-inch skillet (nonstick), heat the oil over moderately high heat.
Add the onion, celery and green pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in beef and cook 4 minutes longer or until no longer pink.
Add the tomatoes with their juices, the ketchup and Worcestershire sauce, salt and black pepper.
Cook, stirring often, 4 minutes more or until the flavors are well blended.
Then stir in the vinegar. Place the bun on plates and divide mixture among them.
Yields 4 sandwiches.

title: st. louis salad
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Cut in pieces.
Chop broccoli.
Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onion, bacon and cheese. Mix sugar and mayonnaise together; add to vegetable mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight to blend.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chinese barbecue spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut spareribs into individual ribs and arrange on rack in baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush ribs lightly with the mixture. Bake 30 minutes longer and turn ribs.
Brush with more sauce and bake 30 minutes longer or until ribs are nicely browned.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue deer ribs
directions: Cut up ribs.
Cook real slow in a large pan covered overnight in water.
Next morning, let cool.
Remove as much fat as possible. Remove meat from bones.
Put meat back in pan.
Cook about 2 hours on low to medium heat until water is gone.
Mix barbecue sauce, onions, meat tenderizer, garlic salt, lemon pepper and Worcestershire sauce in separate bowl, then add to meat.
Cook on low for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves at least 10 people.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, Crisco and salt.
Fork beat egg; add water and vinegar.
Stir well with
fork.
Add a little at a time to flour mixture.
Roll and	put
in
pie
pan.
This should make crusts for 6 pies.
These	crusts	freeze well.
Put wax paper between crusts and they don't stick together.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add sugar.
Cut cherries and marshmallows. Mash cream cheese; work it in the mayonnaise to make a smooth mixture.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pan and freeze at least 3 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and rinse in cold water, drain.
Peel cucumbers and cut all vegetables in bite size pieces.
Grate Parmesan and toss all ingredients.
Refrigerate, preferably overnight.

title: oatmeal no bake cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl the oats and cocoa.
In a large pan or skillet, put sugar, butter and milk.
Let it start boiling and stir good.
When it starts boiling hard, boil one minute.
Remove from heat; add to oatmeal mix and add peanut butter.
Stir until well mixed, then drop by tablespoonfuls on the pan.
Always have your pan lined with wax paper ready.
Place a piece of wax paper on a plate also.
Dip a teaspoon in a cup of water to flatten. Yields 20 to 22 cookies.

title: pasta salad with tomatoes and grilled salmon
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, Set aside. Roast peppers, cool, peel and dice. Combine olive oil, herb seasoning and lemon juice in a large bowl. Add prepared vegetables and pasta, toss well and chill. When ready to serve, brush salmon fillets with a little olive oil and sprinkle lightly with seasoning blend. Grill fillets 3-4 minutes per side on medium heat. Serve hot with pasta salad.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Let peppers stand for 2 hours.
Drain well and add vinegar and sugar.
Boil until it jells and can while hot.
Makes 3 pints.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water and let oats set for 20 minutes.
Next add margarine and both sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients and flour.
Pour into well greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
This makes a small cake.
For a big cake double your recipe.
Cover cake with your favorite pecan or walnut icing.

title: italian hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage until done; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients (except cheese) with meat.
Do not precook macaroni.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°; top with cheese for last 15 minutes of baking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Press ground beef into bottom of 2 1/2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with canned milk, salt and pepper. Slice potatoes over milk; slice onions over potatoes; cover with mushroom soup. Bake covered at 350 degrees for 1 hour until potatoes are done.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer.
Combine oats, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed.
Stir in raisins (optional) and nuts.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Mix rice, onion soup, beef consomme, and mushrooms together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Cook noodles and ground beef first.
Mix together all ingredients except 1 bag of Mozzarella cheese which will be spread on top close to the end of cooking.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes two 11 3/4 x 9 3/8 x 2 3/8-inch pans.

title: luby's tortilla soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to boil. Crush tomatoes by hand. Add juice to broth. Add cumin, garlic, salt, pepper, corn and cheese. Bring to boil again. Dissolve cornstarch in water. Add to boiling soup, slowly. While soup simmers, saute beef in skillet with onion and drain. Turn soup off. Add meat mixture and 1/2 tortilla strips. Heat oil in skillet. Add remaining strips. Fry until crusty. Garnish soup when serving.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix, press into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes, remove from pan.
Serve with mushroom sauce.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion until soft in butter.
Put aside.
Put soup in 2 to 3-quart casserole (no water).
Add melted butter, onion and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Add cooked rice.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts.
Melt butter and drizzle all over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine fruit.
Dump in dry pudding mix.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Serve.

title: tasty potato soup
directions: Cook ham hock until done. Drop potatoes in broth. Cook until done. Add onion. Mix water and flour until dissolved. Pour into mixture. Add margarine. Simmer 10 minutes. Good with cornbread.

title: oatmeal delights
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder and stir into creamed mixture. Add oats, vanilla, chocolate pieces, raisins and nuts and mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 - 15 minutes. Makes about 12 dozen.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs over melted butter.
Press down with fork. Sprinkle coconut evenly, then the chips and pecans.
Drizzle on milk.
Cook until coconut browns.

title: raw relish
directions: Grind all vegetables with food chopper.
Add salt; let stand for 2 hours.
Drain off liquid; let stand in colander until well drained.
Mix vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Mix this with vegetables; pack in jars and seal.
Do not cook!

title: egg nog
directions: Add whipped cream and nutmeg just before serving.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in two 9-inch pans for 30 minutes or in one 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes.

title: calzone
directions: Let dough rise.
Roll dough on a floured surface into a rectangle.
Spray baking sheet with Pam.
Combine ground beef, cheese, barbecue sauce, parsley, basil and oregano; mix well. Spread mixture in a strip in the center of the dough.
Fold sides of dough over filling, overlapping edges.
Pinch together to seal seams and ends.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: fisherman's best spread
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over cold water; let stand for 1 minute.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Blend in sour cream and Thousand Island dressing.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 6 cup mold or bowl; chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet sour hot pickles
directions: Pour liquid off pickles.
Pour sugar on pickles in same jar. Shake to get all of sugar in.
Add hot sauce.
Shake and let sit for 3 days.
Good!!!

title: kiwi raspberry finale
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites and salt until mixture holds soft peaks.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding sugar mixture until mixture holds stiff peaks.
Beat in vinegar and vanilla.

title: homemade pie filling - blueberry(white house)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan and add all other ingredients.
Cook until thickened.

title: spoon bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine cornmeal, flour and salt.
Stir in scalded milk. Beat well to prevent lumping.
Add butter and eggs and beat thoroughly until mixture is smooth.
Sprinkle baking powder over top and quickly beat in.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wheat-free zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Sift flours together 6 times, then combine with other dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla and milk. Stir in dry ingredients and mix.
Fold in zucchini.
Pour into a well-greased angel cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal refrigeration cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add vanilla, then flour, combined with baking soda.
Add oatmeal.
Form into 2 long rolls.
Roll each on chocolate shots, then roll in wax paper. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut 1/4 inch and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: glazed cornish hens
directions: In small saucepan, combine preserves, butter and liqueur. Heat, stirring, until well blended.
Wash and dry hens and place in roasting pan.
Baste hens with apricot glaze.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°, basting frequently.

title: lemon cheese bake(3 pies)
directions: Mix jello and boiling water and refrigerate until cool. Whip chilled Carnation and slowly add sugar. Add cream cheese. Add jello mixture. Pour in pie crusts. Put whipping cream on top.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Brown ground meat in a little oil.
Strain the tomatoes and add a little oil to the pulp.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 40 minutes.
Boil elbow macaroni as per directions and add to sauce and mix.

title: cranberry-peach cobbler
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in juice. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in peaches and cranberries.
Cook, uncovered, until cranberry skins pop, about 5 minutes.

title: italian style chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in pot and cover with cold water.
When water boils add vegetables and seasonings.
Let simmer until meat falls off bone and vegetables are well done.
Keep adding enough water to keep chicken covered.
Remove chicken and vegetables from pot. Mash vegetables fine and return both to pot.
When mixture boils again, add Egg Pastina (I use Ronzoni brand) and continue simmering about 1/2 hour.

title: festive punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl or very large pan.
Serves 100.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan; flour.
Beat sugar and eggs until thickened and pale.
Stir in oil.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon; stir in egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Spoon batter into pan; bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat egg white until it forms a peak.
Add sugar and beat again.
Scald 1/2 cup milk and pour over egg mixture.
Set aside to cool.
Beat butter and Crisco.
Pour liquid mixture over creamed shortening and beat again.
Add vanilla to taste.
Mixture will curdle but keep beating until mixture is smooth and creamy.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Using the apple corer, slice apples and place in either the deep-dish baker or the 9 x 13 baker.
Mix remaining dry ingredients well.
Add melted margarine.
Press this mixture (should be moist and sticky) onto apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: top-of-stove macaroni and cheese
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook macaroni in boiling water for about 8 minutes; drain.
Add soup mix, milk and margarine.
Cook and stir for about 5 minutes, until sauce thickens.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Add wine vinegar and jars of sharp cheese and garlic salt.
Mix together until well blended.

title: cheese-mushroom quiche
directions: Use a 10-inch quiche pan.
Spread cheese, then bacon, then mushrooms in pan.
In blender, mix remaining ingredients and pour mixture in pan.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let stand 4 to 5 minutes before serving.

title: quick cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving.

title: honey of a fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa and cornstarch.
Blend well.
Add honey and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve over ice cream or other desserts. Can be served warm or cold.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Delicious!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread slices in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix
together
eggs,
grated
cheese, salt, pepper, dry mustard, sausage and milk.
Pour over bread.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Cook, covered, in
oven for 20 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: mushroom hamburger steak
directions: Make hamburger into patties, mixing and rolling hamburger in flour.
Spray skillet with nonstick spray.
Cook hamburgers until almost done.
Mix soup and milk together.
Drain excess grease from hamburgers and pour mushroom mixture over hamburgers.
Simmer until hamburgers are done and mushroom gravy has thickened.

title: italian cream cake and icing
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda; let stand.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk and vanilla. Fold in egg whites.
Gently stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: fiesta corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook beef or sausage until broken up and browned.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and peppers; cook until tender.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients except cheese.
Add meat mixture.
Pour half the mixture into greased 9 x 16 x 3-inch pan.
Cover with cheese slices.
Pour remaining mixture over cheese.
Bake for 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: snow cap lemon pie
directions: Bake and cool pastry shell; set aside.
In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, butter, lemon peel, lemon juice, egg yolks and milk.
Stir and cook until thick, about 5 to 10 minutes; cool. Fold in sour cream.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.
Garnish with lemon slices and or chopped pecans.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, melt butter in oven.
Remove pan from oven.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add milk; stir until dough forms.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Coat with flour.
Knead lightly about 10 times.
Roll into 8-inch square.
With floured knife, cut into 18 sticks.
Dip each into melted butter, coating. Arrange in pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions using seasoning packet. Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients in greased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and marshmallows.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
When mixed up, mix in M&M's and peanuts.

title: shrimp a'la pape'
directions: Mix milk, eggs and sherry.
Dip the peeled and deveined shrimp in the egg and then in the crumbs.
Then dip in egg mixture and crumbs the second time.
Top each shrimp with bacon slice and crushed garlic.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Then broil until bacon browns and is crisp.

title: rabbit cutlets
directions: Dress and clean bird carefully.
Place the turkey in a baking pan, add water, salt and pepper.
Bird can be stuffed with your favorite stuffing if desired.
Bake in medium hot oven, allowing about 20 minutes for each pound of weight.
Baste the turkey with butter frequently, because wild birds are usually more lean than domestic fowl.
Thicken the liquid into a gravy before serving.

title: tropical surprise
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased, 9x13 inch pan in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool.
For Frosting mix together the Cool Whip, pineapple and pudding mix.
Spread over cooled cake. Refrigerate.

title: pimento mushroom sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat and stir until hot.

title: crab pasta quicky
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
After pasta is tender, add drained crab meat and stir.
Let stand 3 minutes. Serve with tossed salad for complete, fast meal.

title: turkey onion stew
directions: Wash turkey thighs; pat dry with paper towel.
Brown slightly in 1/4 cup oil.
Peel onions and leave whole.
Place 2 thighs in the bottom of a Dutch oven.
Add 6 onions on top.
Place remaining thighs on the onions, finishing with the remaining onions.
Add garlic, pickling spices (tied in cheesecloth), remaining oil, vinegar, tomatoes, tomato paste and sugar.
Cover tightly; bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low; simmer for 2 to 2 1/4 hours, or until meat is tender and liquid is reduced to a delicious sauce. Remove cheesecloth bag of spices.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Make crust of 2 cups vanilla wafer crumbs and 1 stick of melted margarine.
Press into 9-inch pie plate and chill.
Blend milk and lemon juice until thick.
Partially thaw frozen peaches. Put them into blender and blend for a few seconds until smooth. Pour peaches into milk mixture and blend well.
Fold in dessert topping with spoon and pile into crumb crust.
Very good.

title: zucchini casserole(makes 24 servings; prep time: 12 minutes)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 11 pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until top becomes golden.
Let stand for a time.
Serve in small square pieces.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, pepper, eggs, sugar, and salt together. Pour into a greased 5 qt casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers over top and pour butter over crackers. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Place in a baking dish and sprinkle on crackers.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: spicy jello
directions: Melt red hots in hot water.
Pour over jello and add applesauce.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Put salmon in large bowl; remove bones.
Stir in egg, flour, meal and chopped medium onion and mix all together.
Use teaspoon to spoon out.
Use hot oil in deep fryer.
Spoon in salmon. Remove when brown.
Check first one to make sure it's done inside and out; if not cook longer.

title: famous crullers
directions: Beat egg yolks until frothy; add half and half; beat again. Add sugar, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Last, add flour, a little at a time, until dough is on the tough side, like for noodles. Work it smooth.

title: easy italian crust pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease 12-inch pizza pan; Sprinkle with flour.
In a large skillet lightly brown ground beef; drain. In a small bowl, combine 1 c flour, italian seasoning, salt, pepper, milk and eggs; blend until smooth.
Pour batter into greased pan, tilting pan so batter covers bottom.
Spoon beef over batter, top with onions and mushrooms.
Bake at 425° for 25-30 min. on the lowest oven rack.
In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce and oregano; spoon over pizza.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake an additional 10-15 min.

title: bottom round roast
directions: Mix turnip, celery, carrots, potatoes, beef and mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and water.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, garlic powder, bay leaf, Worcestershire and sliced onion.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours, very tightly sealed in a deep aluminum roaster.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken and Veg-All in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk, margarine and pepper.
Pour on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Brown on top.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breasts until thin, then dip in egg and bread crumbs, coating both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Saute in oil until golden brown on both sides.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Top with tomato sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Saute sliced mushrooms in oil and place over chicken. Top with Mozzarella and bake in preheated oven until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; mix with beaten egg.
Add chopped onion.
Mash crackers fine.
Add teaspoon baking powder.
Make 8 patties. Brown in about an inch of hot vegetable oil on each side until brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook onions in margarine for 15 minutes or until onions are clear.
Add broccoli and cook another 10-15 minutes.
Add soups and mix
well with wire whisk.
Mixture will be a little lumpy. Cook another 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 of large jar of Cheez Whiz.
Use regular or jalapeno according to your taste. Melt the cheese well, but do not re-cook.
Serves 7-10 people.

title: carrot special
directions: Cook carrots for 7 minutes; drain.
Combine tomato soup, sugar, vinegar and oil.
Add carrots and stir to coat/cover. Slice green peppers and onion crosswise for garnish on top.

title: crock-pot texas chili
directions: Brown hamburger and put in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on low heat and let the crock-pot do the rest!!

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
Turn onto floured surface and knead well.
May be pinched off or cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan.
Gently pat tops with meat grease (this helps them brown).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon fish roll-ups
directions: In a medium bowl combine rice, cheese, broccoli and lemon mixture.
Divide mixture among 8 fish fillets.
Roll up and place seam side down in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with remaining sauce and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Blend until smooth cream cheese and powdered sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour on crust. Mix together and boil for one minute, stirring constantly 1 cup sugar, 1 cup water and 3 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Fold in 2 pints, fresh, sliced strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: quick chess pie
directions: Beat for 5 minutes.
(This is the key.)
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini stir-fry
directions: Fry 3 slices bacon, remove from pan.
Add zucchini (peeled), onion, tomato and 1 cup rice.
Stir-fry until tender.
Add crumbled bacon.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: sheath cake
directions: Put the oleo, water, oil and cocoa into a pan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture over flour and sugar. Add milk, eggs, soda and vanilla and mix well.
Bake on a large greased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
Frost if desired.

title: crawfish jambalaya(crawfish jambalaya in hitachi rice cooker)
directions: Wash rice and drain.
Place ingredients in Hitachi Rice cooker with rice.
Do not add any water.
Season to taste.
Start rice cooker.
Let it cook on complete cycle.
Keep on warm 1/2 hour.

title: crock-pot deer meat
directions: Place 1/2 cup water on high in crock-pot before starting. Add a dash of garlic salt and black pepper to water. (Gets it smelling good.) Salt and pepper cubed pieces of deer meat (garlic salt if desired). Do not worry about too much salt, because the can of soup, flour and water will cook it away. Have hot oil in frying pan and as you flour each piece of meat, brown quickly only turning once. Do not try to brown too many pieces at once. Place 6 to 8 pieces at a time into crock-pot, spacing around in a single layer. Continue this process until all pieces are in the pot.

title: onion dill bread
directions: Put the dry ingredients in flour sifter, except onion and dill, with one cup of flour and sift in a large mixing bowl.
Mix yeast with warm water; let activate about 12 to 15 minutes.
Add egg and margarine; beat well until blended.
Add buttermilk, onion, dill and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead and let rise until double in bulk.
Stir down, divide in half and press down into 2 well greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: potato flake cookies(yields 475 to 500 cookies)
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add flavoring and eggs. Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with a #40 scoop.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Do not brown.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Heat oleo and cocoa. Mix in Coca-Cola. Heat on stove almost until boiling. Mix sugar, flour, soda, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Add marshmallows. Add boiling mixture to other ingredients.

title: dick howell's hot slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat to a boil.
Boil for 20 minutes. Sterilize jars and fill and seal.
Makes 9 pints.

title: lemon parsley salmon
directions: Thaw salmon if frozen.
Salt the cavity.
Put garlic, parsley, butter slices and lemon inside cavity of salmon.
Put in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes per 1-inch depth of fish.
Salmon will flake when done.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Brown chicken slowly in medium-hot butter in a skillet, turning as necessary with kitchen tongs.
Remove chicken to a shallow baking dish.
Cook celery and onion in the butter until tender, but not brown.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° (slow) for 45 minutes to an hour or until thickest pieces are fork-tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and cream cheese.
Add sugar gradually.
Add 2 eggs and beat.
Then add flour and eggs alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 3/4 hours at 300°.
Start with cold oven.

title: kiwi pie
directions: Blend Marshmallow Creme and creme de menthe in bowl.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread in pie shell.
Arrange kiwi slices over top.
Chill until serving time.

title: spinach souffl
directions: Chop first 3 ingredients in 1-inch pieces. Add next 6 ingredients and mix well. Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish or 2 (8-inch) baking dishes. Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Let set 20 minutes before cutting into serving pieces. Can be frozen. Makes wonderful side or tasty meatless main dish.

title: festive fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken in lime juice, garlic and seasonings for 15 minutes.
Cook chicken in oil 2 to 3 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add onion and peppers.
Continue cooking 3 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in salsa.
Spoon onto tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Yield: 4 servings.
Preparation time: 20 minutes (including marinating).
Cooking time:
6 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add 1 cup starter and 4 cups flour, sugar and salt.
Cover with cloth, let rise in warm place until double in size.
Then mix 1 cup flour and soda.
Stir this into dough, adding enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on a flour dusted board until smooth and shiny.
Shape dough into half loaf sizes; place in greased bread pans.
Place in warm place until again doubled in size.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Brush top with melted butter.

title: carrie's chocolate sauce
directions: Cook all but the chocolate and vanilla together until thick. Add chocolate; stir until melted.
Add vanilla.

title: cinnamon sour cream cake
directions: Place a graham cracker square on the plate.
Using the pastry bag, make an outline of frosting on the plate surrounding the edges of the graham cracker.
Stand 4 graham crackers upright in the frosting to form walls.
The walls should be standing on the plate, not on the bottom cracker.
Use the pastry bag to run a line of frosting up and down each corner and around the base. Children should decorate these frosted areas now before the frosting sets.
Doors and windows may be decorated now or later.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together all ingredients; roll into balls.
Mold into a muffin pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Let sit for at least 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Use inexpensive yellow cake mix.
Use oil and eggs as directed.
Substitute 3 mashed ripe bananas for liquid (no milk or water).
Bake per mix instructions in loaf pan.

title: soddy daisy sandwich special
directions: Place 2 helpings of butter on 1 side of each bread slice. Place cheese on top of butter.
Place in toaster oven, cheese side up, until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven, put both slices together and enjoy.

title: chicken in herb sauce
directions: Cook celery in butter until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in flour, chives, rosemary, chervil and tarragon.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Heat through. Serve on toast.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp patty shells
