directions: Use double boiler.
Make white sauce according to package directions.
Warm milk before adding sauce mix; stir constantly.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Let warm to room temperature and serve.
This is a great dip or sauce for crackers, cheese, fruit, etc.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Season refried beans with 1/2 package taco seasoning and spread in bottom of 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Add chopped olives. Spread guacamole over this.
Mix 1/2 package taco seasoning with sour cream and mayonnaise; spread over other ingredients.
Top with chopped green onions, then tomato, then grated cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: apricot salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over pineapple.
Let set 30 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Mix well with spoon.
Add pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water and baking soda over dates; cool.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs and add to date mixture.
Sift and measure dry ingredients.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add vanilla and stir in walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg until smooth.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Make crisscross pattern on cookies with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Put flour into large pan; form it outward to the edge so as to make it look like a bowl.
Dissolve dry yeast in 3/4 cup warm water (deduct warm water amount from total liquid in the recipe).
Melt 5 tablespoons shortening in separate pan.
Pour 1 1/2 quarts warm water in bowl, less that used in yeast.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix until dissolved; add salt until it no longer tastes sweet.
Pour the water into the pan of flour.
Pour in the melted shortening. Add the dissolved yeast.
With your hand, start to mix the flour. Mix until sticky.
You will have to add more flour until it is no longer sticky.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Add all
ingredients; simmer for 20 minutes.
Good over chicken, spareribs or hamburg barbecue.

title: brunch strata
directions: Place cubes in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
On top of bread, layer onion, ham and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Pour over ingredients in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: bob's barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer onions and drippings 20 minutes until onions are clear. In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Simmer together with onions and drippings for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Boil peppers until tender.
Mix everything together.
Stuff into peppers.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: honey buns
directions: Measure into mixing bowl the warm water.
Add, stirring to dissolve, the yeast.
Stir in the milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and flour; mix well.
Turn onto well floured board and knead.
Put into greased bowl; let rise until double in size. Punch down; let rise again.
Roll into rectangle as for cinnamon rolls.
Spread with Honey Filling.
Slice into 1-inch pieces and place in muffin tins.
Place more Honey Filling on each bun as they bake.
These should not get real brown.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Bring milk to boiling point.
Add grated cheese, pimiento and other ingredients to hot milk.
Stir to blend.
Remove from heat; add salt to taste.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: broccoli brown rice
directions: In a large skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray, saute rice until brown. Add broth and garlic. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 40 minutes. Stir in broccoli, salt and pepper. Cover and cook 5 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Dissolve sugar in oil.
Add eggs (one at a time; blend each in well).
Add dry ingredients; carrots last.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 15-inch greased pan.
Don't overbake.
Bake at 350°.

title: sparkle punch
directions: Remove sherbet from container and place into punch bowl.
Pour liquids over sherbet.

title: fluffy moist stuffing
directions: Prepare bread crumbs by toasting in a 325° oven for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Place fat, onion and celery in a skillet and saute until onion is transparent.
Pour over toasted bread crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well, using a fork. Place in a greased pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all items together and put into a greased casserole dish. Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven.
Add topping.

title: creamy mashed potato bake
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, milk and garlic powder; mix well. Spoon half the mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with 2/3 cup onions and 1/2 cup cheese. Top with remaining potato mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until hot. Top with remaining onions and cheese. Bake 5 to 7 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: taggart's world famous peanut butter candy
directions: Pour the milk in a large saucepan.
Sift the sugar on top of the milk.
Heat at medium-high, stirring constantly to help melt the sugar.
When the sugar has completely melted, continue to heat until a slow boil occurs and some slight scorching is evident.
Be sure to continue stirring to prevent burning on the bottom.
Remove from the heat and add in the peanut butter, marshmallow cream and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered dish and let cool before cutting.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine milk, cream
cheese, butter, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Cook
over
low	heat,
stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Add corn. Heat until warm.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Mix celery, rice, water and soups in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay the chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle the soup mix over the chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours, depending on how dry you want the rice mixture to be.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Bake at 350°.
Do not open oven during baking.

title: easy butterscotch-chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set.
Let stand 2 minutes; remove to wire racks.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix together with potato masher or hands.
Roll into balls or bars and freeze on foil covered cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and 1 large Hershey bar in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Place back on foil; add walnuts to top while chocolate is still warm.
Put back in freezer until set, then in airtight containers.
I usually double this recipe because a can of Eagle Brand milk is one cup.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Puree first four ingredients in blender.
Pour into a large saucepan and add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.
Serves 4.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients for crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup. Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Mix the rest of the ingredients with mixer.
Add to baked crumbs; put leftover cup of crumb mixture on top of cheese mix and bake at 350° for 25 more minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, then vanilla.
Add flour and baking soda, a little at a time.
Fold in mashed bananas lightly, then chopped nuts.
Put into 2 or 3 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until center top is no longer soft, but set.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together 2 cups flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Stir in apples.
Combine walnuts and 1 tablespoon flour; stir into batter.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool; spread with the following topping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add to broccoli mixture and refrigerate 2 hours or more.

title: creamy custard pie
directions: Scald 1 cup of milk.
Mix dry ingredients with remaining milk.
Add to hot milk and cook until custard coats one spoon, about 15 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir to blend.
Remove from heat.
When partially cooled, pour into baked pie shell. Chill thoroughly before serving.
Contains 81 calories per serving.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs well.
Beat in sugar.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture; spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add to above mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soak the yeast in 1/4 c. warm water, sift together the flour, sugar, salt, soda and dill seed.
Make a hole in center of the flour mixture, add the cottage cheese, egg, butter and yeast.
Mix ingredients thoroughly and let dough rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Shape into 2 loaves and place on cookie sheet. Let rise again and bake at 350° for 35 min.
After loaves are removed from the oven, butter the top and sprinkle with salt.

title: louisiana chicken gumbo
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cool and debone.
In a large cooking pot, put oil.
As oil gets hot, add flour slowly to oil, making a brown roux.
Add onions, bell pepper and celery.
Cook until soft. Put chicken back in pot.
Add 1 gallon of water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Season to taste.
Add parsley and onion tops (optional). Serve in soup plates over rice.
Serve, also, with garlic French bread.

title: poke cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
While cake is hot, poke holes in cake and pour over the cake in a ribbon fashion the cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk.
Let cake cool in refrigerator.
Use one carton Cool Whip for icing and top with coconut.

title: theresa's hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.
Mix Bisquick, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Spread evenly into pan.
Mix 1/3 cup cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over.
Do not mix. Bake 40 minutes.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix.
Pour
cream cheese mixture on top of cake mixture and bake
for
55 minutes at 325°.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: never-fail yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water in bowl.
In another bowl, beat egg, sugar and shortening together; mix well.
Add cold water and mix with yeast.
Add flour and salt and mix well.
Place in greased bowl; grease top.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight. Take out amount you want to use.
Flour and roll out.
Cut biscuit size.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Grease top with butter.
Bake at 400°.
Remaining dough must be used in 3 days.
May be baked at one time and frozen.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt over medium-high heat until boil, stirring constantly.
Then cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Pour over corn and nuts.
Mix thoroughly, then bake 1 hour in 200° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add extracts.
Beat eggs until light and lemon colored. Add sifted together flour, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spoon mixture into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan lined with greased brown paper (optional).
Bake in a 325° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Add glaze, if desired, or cool in pan before turning out on a cooling rack.

title: eggplant pie
directions: Flute the edge of pie crust to make a high rim; set aside. In skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add eggplant.
Cover; cook 5 minutes.
Remove eggplant; set aside.
Add beef, onion and garlic to skillet.
Cook, stirring often, until meat is browned, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain fat from skillet.
Add tomato sauce, celery leaves, parsley, oregano and pepper to skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Stir in eggplant.
Remove skillet from heat; cool slightly.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes or until pie is golden brown.
Sprinkle cheese over surface.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cool 5 minutes.
If you enjoy pizzas, you will enjoy this pie!

title: south-of-france vegetable soup(low-fat)
directions: In a 4-quart pot, combine first 14 ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover; reduce the heat to medium and simmer for 20 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Stir in the pasta.
Cover, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until the pasta is tender.
Serves 4.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: san francisco stir-fry
directions: *Tip:
If currant jelly is not available, 1/2 cup apple jelly and 3 tablespoons lemon juice may be substituted.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef with other ingredients.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and minced onion. Roll into balls and broil in oven, turning until all sides are browned.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Mix in dry taco mix.
Set aside for 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients except lettuce, Doritos and dressing.
Add just before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: caramel pecans
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar and sour cream.
Let it come to hard boil and put in pecans and vanilla.
Pour on wax paper, sprayed.

title: banana split cake
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with crackers.
Pour pudding over crackers.
Spread sliced bananas over pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip. Spread strawberries over Cool Whip.
Spread pineapple over strawberries. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: lasagne #3
directions: Rinse, drain, crumble and measure tofu.
Put into bowl and add next three ingredients.
Mix together well with hands.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts (boil) until tender.
Combine deboned chicken, Veg-All and cream of chicken soup in large mixing bowl. Add thickened gravy, mix. Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Use other 2 pie crusts for top crust.
Place on top of pies. Brush tops with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Freezes well.
Freeze before you cook.)

title: one-pot black pepper gingerbread
directions: Measure the flour in a 4-cup measuring cup and thoroughly mix in the baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, mustard, pepper and ginger. Set aside.
In a large heavy saucepan, melt the butter.
Remove from heat and add the sugar, molasses, coffee and eggs, beating with a whisk until smooth, and beat in the boiling water.

Pour batter into a greased and flour-dusted 9-inch square baking pan. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes, until a tester inserted in center comes out with just a few crumbs clinging to it. Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Invert, remove from pan and cool completely right side up.
Serve warm or completely cool with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to first mixture until well blended. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes (until center is done) in 2 loaf pans or 1 (11 x 13-inch) pan.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream Crisco until soft. Add sugar slowly and beat until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add vanilla and mix at low speed.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yam-praline pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugars, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt in large mixing bowl. Blend in sweet potatoes. Gradually stir in milk and half and half. Pour into unbaked pastry shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer. Sprinkle Praline Topping over surface of pie. Continue baking 25 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: red curry shrimp(thai)
directions: Heat olive oil in large saucepan over high heat.
Add onion and garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add coconut milk and curry paste and cook, stirring constantly for 3 minutes.
Add lime leaves, basil and fish sauce; bring to boil.
Add squash, cream, red bell pepper and flour/water mixture and return to boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until sauce is thick, about 15 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Bring to boil; let boil 2 minutes.
Transfer curry to a bowl.
Garnish with basil and serve with white rice.

title: crusty beefeater sandwich
directions: Brown meat, add onions.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, catsup and chili powder with meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vanilla wafer bundt cake
directions: Mix eggs, one at a time, with sugar; add milk, then add one box vanilla wafers and add coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes (Bundt cake pan, greased and floured).

title: western hash
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 25 or 30 minutes until rice is tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 pound loaf pan, Bundt pan or muffin tins.
Cream sugars and butter.
Blend in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to batter. Combine buttermilk and soda and add to batter.
Add mashed bananas, vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Pour into prepared pan and bake approximately 1 hour, until toothpick in center comes out clean.
If making muffins, baking time is 15 minutes.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Drain and seed peppers.
Cut into lengthwise slices and line bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Press grated cheese in plate over peppers.
Beat eggs, adding salt and red pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
After removing from oven, slice into small wedges.
Leave in pie plate and serve as finger food.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Add nuts and coconut, mixing well.
Blend 1 cup butter and 1/3 cup cocoa together in bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients with eggs, mixing well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over hot cake.
Combine remaining ingredients and 1/3 cup cocoa and 1/2 cup butter in bowl, mixing well.
Spread over cool cake.
Yields 24 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk, in a microwave dish. Add enough milk to cover.
Don't cover with lid.
Bake in microwave on high for 10 minutes.
Stir as it cooks.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: hash brown skillet breakfast
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Drain well, reserving drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Heat drippings in pan; add frozen potatoes.
Cook over low heat until underside is crisp and lightly brown.
(Do not turn over.)

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: individual clam bake
directions: We once had a young horse that Darrel trained to run under the roof of the open end of the barn.
This was while we lived up on Grandma and Grandpa Kimbrel's place.

Well, he would let our friends ride and neglect to tell them to duck when they got to the barn. That was about the same time that he took each of us out to the patch, one at a time, to eat the "first" ripe watermelon. It took us a couple of years to catch onto to that one.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all and cook slowly in crust for 30 to 45 minutes. Can be topped with meringue.

title: hot salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: apple-raisin cole slaw
directions: Mix all together in large bowl; set aside.

title: mock cream cheese
directions: Mix first two ingredients in blender.
Remove from blender and stir in vanilla supplement.
Let chill.

title: spinach toss
directions: To make dressing, use a blender container.
Combine oil, sugar, onion, vinegar, mustard and celery seed.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Keep covered and chill.
In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
In a large salad bowl, combine spinach, mushrooms, eggs and bacon.
Pour dressing over salad; toss lightly.

title: sugar-free layered pudding
directions: Spread 7 graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Prepare pudding using only 3 cups of milk.
Fold in 8 ounces of Cool Whip. Add well drained pineapple.
Spread half of pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Add 7 more graham crackers and spread remaining pudding mixture over top.
Add 7 more crackers.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Can top with chopped pecans and cherries. Serves 12.

title: praline squares
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs by hand.
Add eggs in 3 parts and then pecans.
Spray jelly roll pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: plain sponge cake
directions: Beat the yolks of eggs with two cups of sugar.

Stir in gradually 1 cup of sifted flour and the whites of 4 eggs, beaten stiff, then a cup of sifted flour in which two teaspoons of baking powder has been stirred and lastly, a scant teacupful of boiling water, stirred in a little at a time.
Flavor and add salt. However thin the mixture may seem do not add any more flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then 375° for 10 minutes.

title: jim's barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and garlic and cook over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cola beverage and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cola.
This sauce is excellent for meats and poultry. Great for Memorial Day or the 4th of July.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all together and blend in butter; put on top of sweet potatoes and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: leeann chin's mandarin pork
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Cut pork into matchsticks (1/8 x 2-inch slices).
Toss pork, 1 tablespoon oil, cornstarch, salt, 1 teaspoon soy sauce, sugar and white pepper in glass or plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Cut green onions into 2-inch pieces. Cut green pepper, carrots, and bamboo shoots into 1/8-inch strips. Heat wok until 1 or 2 drops of water bubble and skitter when sprinkled in wok.
Add 1/4 cup oil; rotate wok to coat side.
Add pork, ginger root and garlic; stir-fry until pork is no longer pink.
Add green pepper, bamboo shoots and carrots; stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir in green onions, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and chili paste.
Makes 5 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook in microwave on high 2 minutes.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes.
Add 1/2 tsp baking soda and 1 tsp. vanilla.

title: pea salad
directions: Tear and shred lettuce; place in the bottom of serving dish. Layer the fresh vegetables.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over top of the vegetables. Sprinkle the peas over the dressing and cover with cheese and Bac*Os.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Add sugar gradually; stir in milk and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Boil gently for 8 minutes.
Watch, as it burns easily.
Makes 1 1/2 cups (8 servings).
Use on ice cram.

title: mexican punch
directions: Fill gallon jar with dry mixture.
Add a little water; mix well.
Add pineapple juice, lemon juice and water to fill the jar. Makes 1 gallon.
Fills 30 punch cups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and put into casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and melted butter and spread on top.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: In a saucepan, heat water to boiling.
Stir in all at once the oil, salt, alum and flour.
Stir until it forms a ball.
Cool a bit and knead until it's smooth.
Add food coloring and/or flavoring, if desired.
Keeps for weeks when stored in a tightly covered container.

title: poppin' fresh tuna biscuits
directions: Bake biscuits as directed.
Combine soup, milk and onion in saucepan.
Cook until smooth.
Fold in celery, tuna and vegetables.
Cook until heated through.
Spoon over biscuits.

title: roman hamburgers
directions: Mix meat with parsley, garlic, oregano, salt, pepper, onion and Parmesan cheese.
Shape into 4 patties.
Grill over hot coals. Top each burger with Mozzarella cheese when meat is cooked through.
Remove when cheese is just melted and place on buttered, toasted Italian bread.

title: pecan pie
directions: Set oven at 375°. Beat eggs slightly in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and melted margarine. Stir in pecans. Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue burger mix
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Add vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: old family recipe beef stew
directions: Place beef in a crock-pot.
Add mushroom soup.
Cook overnight on low.
Serve over mashed potatoes or over toast.

title: sauce for broccoli and asparagus
directions: Blend together.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: chicken spaghetti no. 1
directions: Boil and debone fryers.
Simmer onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in broth.
Heat soups, tomatoes and pimentos together. Boil spaghetti in broth until tender.
Mix all together.
Put in very large casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Place in casserole in order given.
Cover beef with 4 slices bacon strips.
Bake 1 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered, in 350° oven.
Use 2-quart casserole.

title: chicken reuben casserole
directions: In buttered baking dish, layer chicken, sauerkraut and Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake and brown sugar sauce
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs. Beat until fluffy. Mix in apples and carrots. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamy mixture. Bake in greased 13 x 9 cake pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken tenders
directions: Cut breasts in small pieces.
Melt oleo or butter in saucepan. Add about 1 tablespoon of garlic chips to the bread crumbs and also 3 to 4 tablespoons of oregano to bread crumbs.
Season with the salt and pepper.

title: italian cream cake
directions: In a bowl, cream together margarine and shortening. Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes. Frost layers and top with a cream cheese frosting.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce and sweet and sour sauce in crock-pot. Add meatballs.
Cook several hours (at least 2 to 3 hours) on low setting.
Cooking longer is better.

title: finger jello
directions: In a bowl stir until dissolved about 2 minutes. Pour into 9/13 cake pan.

title: california burgers(lo-fat)
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix turkey, onions, celery, red peppers, tomato paste, garlic and black pepper. Form 12 patties. Grill, broil or saute in a nonstick frying pan.
Serve in rolls with lettuce and tomatoes. Serves 12.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed on the package.
Cook and crumble.
Add bacon and chopped vegetables.
Stir in mayonnaise. Chill until served.
It's better if made a day ahead and kept in the refrigerator overnight.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix ingredients well until blended.
If sticky, add confectioners sugar until of a consistency to work with.
After children make their sculpture, they can eat it.

title: randy's favorite haystacks
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients together.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Plop onto waxed paper and let cool slightly.
Keeps really well in the freezer.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise, salt, celery and onion.
Stir well.
Add shrimp.
Pour into molds and chill.
You can use mushroom soup and crab instead of tomato soup and shrimp.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, cube and cook eggplant until tender.
Drain and add salt and pepper.
Mash tomatoes and onions; combine with eggs and cornbread.
Add to eggplant.
If mixture is too thick, add a little milk.
Pour into buttered dish and top with grated cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until done.

title: cuppa cake(english war time cake)
directions: Put raisins, currants, margarine and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, baking powder and flour.
Lastly, add eggs and beat well.
Pour mixture into two 1-pound loaf tins or one 2-pound loaf tin or any old tin, greased and lined.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes for 2-pound tin, 40 minutes for 1-pound tin.
Cool in tins; turn out on wire rack.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Cut meat into bite-sized cubes.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over beef cubes and let stand at room temperature one hour or in refrigerator several hours.
Thread cubes of meat onto a skewer.
(Pineapple chunks may be alternated with the beef cubes.)
Broil about 3 inches from heat 10 to 12 minutes, turning once, or cook over grill or hibachi.
Serve hot as an appetizer or with rice as a main course.

title: double dairy bars
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy and smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until well blended.
Mix flour, soda and salt together, then stir into mixture.
Add oats.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread into ungreased baking pan.
Add filling.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes, until top is lightly browned and springs back when touched with fingertip.
While bars bake, prepare frosting.
As soon as bars come from oven, drizzle or spread frosting over surface.
Cool to room temperature before cutting.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well and pour in two 5 x 9-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: earthquake dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch will run over). Cover bottom with coconut, then layer nuts.
Mix cake and put over nuts.
Mix margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spoon over mix; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
Let stand until cold.
Add the beaten egg.
If dough is too soft to roll, add more flour.
Roll or cut into pieces or strips.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cover and cook for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecued pulled pork sandwiches
directions: Place pork roast in slow cooker, cover and cook on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Remove roast and pull meat into shredded pieces. Pour out any liquid in the pot and combine pork with the remaining ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook on high for 2 hours.
Serve on buns.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in oil.
Add soup and thawed vegetables.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Turn into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and top with noodles.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Or cook in microwave 15 minutes on Medium-high.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 20-30 minutes
(stirring to keep from burning) until slightly thickened. Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: potato casserole 2
directions: Mix margarine, chopped onions, Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper, sour cream and soup together.
Add package of thawed potatoes. Crumble corn flakes or Ritz crackers on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into small squares before serving.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil. Add cabbage. Bring to a boil again. Cook for 5 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: banana split cake
directions: Drain juice from crushed pineapple into shallow dish.
Slice bananas and dip in pineapple juice.

title: heavenly cream
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows.
Let stand overnight.
Just before serving, add whipping cream and nuts.
Fold ingredients together.
Do not stir.

title: irish stew
directions: Brown lamb in oil.
Pour water over lamb.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in skillet.
Top with soup mix and pour in salad dressing and water.
Bake, covered, in moderate 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place banana slices in reserved pineapple juice while mixing rest of salad.
Drain fruit cocktail, mix with rest of ingredients.
Drain bananas before adding to mixture.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Melt butter.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over baked wings and stir.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder; set aside. In a large mixer bowl beat shortening, egg yolks and sugar until creamy.
Add cocoa powder and vanilla.
Add flour a little at a time, alternating with the milk.
Beat until smooth.
Drop dough by 1/2 tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack and let it cool.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Drain beans and fix in baking dish.
Put sausage and onion on top of beans, then tomato soup. Fix instant potatoes according to package and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, mix 1 cup of flour, sugar, ginger, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add water, shortening or margarine and molasses.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour and eggs; beat until blended.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes on wire rack.

title: dee's vegetable soup
directions: In 3 gallon pot, put bite size pieces of hamburger meat in water as it is coming to a boil.
Then add chopped vegetables, frozen vegetables and rest of ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Let it sit overnight in refrigerator and then can be frozen in small containers.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine and brown sugar. Add egg yolk and flour.
Spread in a large, glass 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until barely brown.
Don't overbake.
Lay the Hershey bars on top of hot cake as soon as removed from oven. Spread chocolate over whole cake.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut before cooled.

title: apple salad
directions: Peel apples and cut in blocks; put in jar.
Put milk in quart jar; add pudding.
Stir at once with a fork until dissolved; put lid on.
Shake real good and refrigerate.
Next put jello and water in jar; refrigerate when cool.
In another jar put celery in refrigerator.
Put cream cheese in mixer bowl; at room temperature beat until smooth.
Slowly add condensed milk, vanilla and lemon juice; beat until very fluffy.
Refrigerate in quart jar.

title: herb mustard rub pork roasts
directions: In a small bowl, combine onion, mustard, marjoram, rosemary and pepper.
Spread mixture on all sides of roast.
Cover; refrigerate for 2 hours or up to 24 hours.
Roast or grill meat.

title: ham delight
directions: In a small pot on low heat, combine first 5 ingredients. Let simmer till margarine melts. Spread mustard mixture on both of rolls. Layer ham and cheese. Put top on and cut through individual rolls with electric knife. Put in the pan, cover with foil and bake at 400° for 20 - 30 minutes. Take out and enjoy.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Mix these ingredients together and add your service through a sieve so faults will sift away and cause no one to grieve.
Stir mixture lightly with a son or daughter, making every stroke a prayer.
Pour gently in the pan of kindness, love and care.
Bake slowly in the heart and when done, allow to cool.
Share kindly with thy neighbor.
Serve with the Golden Rule.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken in pieces until tender.
Remove from bone (can add extra chicken).
Cut flour tortillas in fourths; soften in broth.
Line baking pan with tortillas.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Layer half of chicken, green pepper and onion in pan. Put another layer of softened tortillas.
Add remaining chicken, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Mix and pour over cream of chicken soup, golden mushroom soup and tomatoes and green chilies.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and zucchini in salad oil.
Put all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Mix together flour, salt, cocoa, baking powder and sugar in a medium bowl. Stir in milk, butter and vanilla. Mix until smooth. Pour into a well-greased 8X8 pan.

title: candied yams
directions: Butter large deep baking dish well.
Place potatoes in dish. Pour sugars over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and stir carefully.
Cut butter into squares and place over potatoes.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and syrup thickens.
Stir occasionally.
Cover with marshmallows and return to oven until marshmallows melt.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Place flour, paprika and garlic powder in paper bag.
Put chicken pieces in bag and shake until coated.
Pan-fry coated chicken to light brown on both sides.
Place chicken in casserole dish or baking pan.
To drippings, add ketchup and remaining ingredients.
Stir until bubbly.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch oiled baking dish with one-half of tomato slices, cover with one-half of the prepared vegetables, then sprinkle with the rice and remaining vegetables.
Top with remaining tomato slices.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Mix the molasses, brown sugar, salt, mustard and soda in bowl; let set overnight.
Early in the morning, add pork (cut in small pieces), onions (cut in half) and the mixture from the bowl.
Bake for at least 8 hours at 275°.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake as said on box.
When done, poke holes throughout the cake.
Pour caramel topping over cake; then pour the Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let cool; then ice with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate rum truffles
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in 2-quart saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add egg yolks and rum.
Beat with wooden spoon or plastic whisk until well blended.
Pour into bowl.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.
Shape mixture into 36 (1-inch) balls, about 1 teaspoon each.
Roll in cocoa.
Refrigerate several hours or until serving time.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Pour boiling water over rhubarb and let stand 10 minutes, then drain.
Add sugar, water, flour and egg yolks.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Add butter; pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and 1 tablespoon sugar until stiff and add vanilla.
Spread on top of pie.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts florentine
directions: Cook spinach as package directs. In small bowl, combine bread crumbs and basil. Dredge chicken with bread crumbs and basil. Heat oil in large skillet. Brown chicken on both sides. Leave in skillet and spoon spinach evenly over chicken and sprinkle with cheese. Cover and cook over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Drop from a teaspoon into hot grease and fry like doughnuts.

title: butter drop-ins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a baking sheet and set aside.
Cream together Crisco, sugar and milk in a medium bowl at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Drop by level tablespoons onto a baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen cookies.

title: syrup for lemonade
directions: Boil sugar, water and lemon rind for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add juice of lemons.
Bottle and place in refrigerator.
Use 2 tablespoons syrup to 1 glass ice water.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and let set overnight.
Great with baked potatoes, too!

title: "cheese" english monkey
directions: Combine the crumbs, cheese, milk and mustard in a heavy-bottomed pan and heat, stirring, over medium-low heat.
Cook until the cheese has melted and all the ingredients are hot and blended.
Spoon over toast!

title: lemon chicken
directions: Lightly flour chicken and fry in butter until golden brown (approximately 5 minutes each side).
Place in warm oven.
Add 3 tablespoons of butter in pan.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add wine and lemon juice.
Simmer on low 5 minutes.
Add chicken to sauce and cover.
Simmer 5 to 10 more minutes.
Serve with rice.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Grease pan well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Brown under broiler a few minutes on top (note this recipe will fill a 10-inch pie).

title: mic's mints
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
When melted, remove from heat and slowly mix in the sugar, flavor and color.
When it is a nice ball, remove from pan and shape as desired.
Smaller pieces are better due to the richness of the mint.
Makes about 1 pound of candy.

title: chess pie(my mother, mrs. brodie's, recipe)
directions: Melt oleo and mix in vinegar.
Mix, by hand, all other ingredients.
Add oleo and vinegar mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (frozen deep-dish pie crust works well).
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until center of pie is firm.

title: louisiana yam cake
directions: Resift flour with soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg. Into mixing bowl, combine sugar and cooking oil; mix thoroughly. Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add mashed potatoes with dry ingredients and pecans; mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased Bundt or tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Invert on plate and cool.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Mash sweet potatoes/yams with 1/4 cup butter or margarine and 1/2 can of sweetened condensed milk.
Mash until all lumps are gone and mixture is very smooth.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch dish. Combine brown sugar, 1/2 cup butter and remaining milk in a saucepan over low heat.
Heat and stir until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle top with chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Delicious for Christmas.

title: marinade for fish or chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in a Ziploc bag. Shake to mix. Marinate fish or chicken for 30 minutes and drain well. If broiling or grilling, baste with marinade.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, salt and cloves in large mixing bowl.
Lightly beat eggs. Beat in pumpkin and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just to combine.
Spoon into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish; saute onions and mushrooms in oleo.
Add consomme, water, salt and pepper.
Pour rice into mixture and stir.
Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Do not stir.

title: slow cooker lasagna
directions: Cook meat and Italian seasoning in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring until beef crumbles; drain. Combine spaghetti sauce and water in a small bowl.
